51// There are three kinds of ObjectData values.
52//
53// kSmi: The underlying V8 object is a Smi and the data is an instance of the
54// base class (ObjectData), i.e. it's basically just the handle. Because the
55// object is a Smi, it's safe to access the handle in order to extract the
56// number value, and AsSmi() does exactly that.
57//
58// kSerializedHeapObject: The underlying V8 object is a HeapObject and the
59// data is an instance of the corresponding (most-specific) subclass, e.g.
60// JSFunctionData, which provides serialized information about the object.
61//
62// kUnserializedHeapObject: The underlying V8 object is a HeapObject and the
63// data is an instance of the base class (ObjectData), i.e. it basically
64// carries no information other than the handle.
65//
66// kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject: The underlying V8 object is a read-only
67// HeapObject and the data is an instance of ObjectData. For
68// ReadOnlyHeapObjects, it is OK to access heap even from off-thread, so
69// these objects need not be serialized.
70enum ObjectDataKind {
71 kSmi,
72 kSerializedHeapObject,
73 kUnserializedHeapObject,
74 kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject
75};
76
77class AllowHandleAllocationIf {
78 public:
79 explicit AllowHandleAllocationIf(ObjectDataKind kind,
80 JSHeapBroker::BrokerMode mode) {
81 DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode == JSHeapBroker::BrokerMode::kSerialized,((void) 0)
82 kind == kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)((void) 0);
83 if (kind == kUnserializedHeapObject) maybe_allow_handle_.emplace();
84 }
85
86 private:
87 base::Optional<AllowHandleAllocation> maybe_allow_handle_;
88};
89
90class AllowHandleDereferenceIf {
91 public:
92 explicit AllowHandleDereferenceIf(ObjectDataKind kind,
93 JSHeapBroker::BrokerMode mode) {
94 DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode == JSHeapBroker::BrokerMode::kSerialized,((void) 0)
95 kind == kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)((void) 0);
96 if (kind == kUnserializedHeapObject ||
97 kind == kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)
98 maybe_allow_handle_.emplace();
99 }
100
101 explicit AllowHandleDereferenceIf(ObjectDataKind kind) {
102 if (kind == kUnserializedHeapObject ||
103 kind == kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)
104 maybe_allow_handle_.emplace();
105 }
106
107 private:
108 base::Optional<AllowHandleDereference> maybe_allow_handle_;
109};

124namespace {
125bool IsReadOnlyHeapObject(Object object) {
126 DisallowHeapAllocation no_gc;
127 return (object.IsCode() && Code::cast(object).is_builtin()) ||
128 (object.IsHeapObject() &&
129 ReadOnlyHeap::Contains(HeapObject::cast(object)));
130}
131} // namespace

135 ObjectData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage, Handle<Object> object,
136 ObjectDataKind kind)

138 // This assignment ensures we don't end up inserting the same object

145 // It is safe to access read only heap objects and builtins from a
146 // background thread. When we read fileds of these objects, we may create
147 // ObjectData on the background thread even without a canonical handle
148 // scope. This is safe too since we don't create handles but just get
149 // handles from read only root table or builtins table which is what
150 // canonical scope uses as well. For all other objects we should have
151 // created ObjectData in canonical handle scope on the main thread.
152 CHECK_IMPLIES(do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!(broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker
::kDisabled || broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kSerializing
) || (broker->isolate()->handle_scope_data()->canonical_scope
!= nullptr))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kDisabled || broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kSerializing"
" implies " "broker->isolate()->handle_scope_data()->canonical_scope != nullptr"
); } } while (false)

::kDisabled || broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kSerializing
) || (broker->isolate()->handle_scope_data()->canonical_scope
!= nullptr))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kDisabled || broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kSerializing"
" implies " "broker->isolate()->handle_scope_data()->canonical_scope != nullptr"
); } } while (false)
154 broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kSerializing,do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!(broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker
::kDisabled || broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kSerializing
) || (broker->isolate()->handle_scope_data()->canonical_scope
!= nullptr))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kDisabled || broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kSerializing"
" implies " "broker->isolate()->handle_scope_data()->canonical_scope != nullptr"
); } } while (false)
155 broker->isolate()->handle_scope_data()->canonical_scope != nullptr)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!(broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker
::kDisabled || broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kSerializing
) || (broker->isolate()->handle_scope_data()->canonical_scope
!= nullptr))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kDisabled || broker->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kSerializing"
" implies " "broker->isolate()->handle_scope_data()->canonical_scope != nullptr"

263FunctionTemplateInfoData::FunctionTemplateInfoData(
264 JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
265 Handle<FunctionTemplateInfo> object)
266 : HeapObjectData(broker, storage, object),
267 c_function_(v8::ToCData<Address>(object->GetCFunction())),
268 c_signature_(v8::ToCData<CFunctionInfo*>(object->GetCSignature())),
269 known_receivers_(broker->zone()) {
270 auto function_template_info = Handle<FunctionTemplateInfo>::cast(object);
271 is_signature_undefined_ =
272 function_template_info->signature().IsUndefined(broker->isolate());
273 accept_any_receiver_ = function_template_info->accept_any_receiver();
274
275 CallOptimization call_optimization(broker->isolate(), object);
276 has_call_code_ = call_optimization.is_simple_api_call();
277}

283 callback_(v8::ToCData<Address>(object->callback())) {}

299void PropertyCellData::Serialize(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
300 if (value_ != nullptr) return;
301
302 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "PropertyCellData::Serialize");
303 auto cell = Handle<PropertyCell>::cast(object());
304 value_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(cell->value());
305}
306
307void FunctionTemplateInfoData::SerializeCallCode(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
308 if (call_code_ != nullptr) return;
309
310 TraceScope tracer(broker, this,
311 "FunctionTemplateInfoData::SerializeCallCode");
312 auto function_template_info = Handle<FunctionTemplateInfo>::cast(object());
313 call_code_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(function_template_info->call_code())
314 ->AsCallHandlerInfo();
315 call_code_->Serialize(broker);
316}
317
318void CallHandlerInfoData::Serialize(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
319 if (data_ != nullptr) return;
320
321 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "CallHandlerInfoData::Serialize");
322 auto call_handler_info = Handle<CallHandlerInfo>::cast(object());
323 data_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(call_handler_info->data());
324}

326class JSObjectField {
327 public:
328 bool IsDouble() const { return object_ == nullptr; }
329 uint64_t AsBitsOfDouble() const {
330 CHECK(IsDouble())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsDouble())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "IsDouble()"); } } while (false);
331 return number_bits_;
332 }
333 double AsDouble() const {
334 CHECK(IsDouble())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsDouble())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "IsDouble()"); } } while (false);
335 return bit_cast<double>(number_bits_);
336 }
337
338 bool IsObject() const { return object_ != nullptr; }
339 ObjectData* AsObject() const {
340 CHECK(IsObject())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsObject())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "IsObject()"); } } while (false);
341 return object_;
342 }
343
344 explicit JSObjectField(uint64_t value_bits) : number_bits_(value_bits) {}
345 explicit JSObjectField(ObjectData* value) : object_(value) {}
346
347 private:
348 ObjectData* object_ = nullptr;
349 uint64_t number_bits_ = 0;
350};

388 JSHeapBroker* broker, Representation representation,
389 FieldIndex field_index,
390 SerializationPolicy policy = SerializationPolicy::kAssumeSerialized);
391
392 // This method is only used to assert our invariants.
393 bool cow_or_empty_elements_tenured() const;
394
395 private:
396 void SerializeRecursiveAsBoilerplate(JSHeapBroker* broker, int max_depths);
397
398 ObjectData* elements_ = nullptr;
399 bool cow_or_empty_elements_tenured_ = false;
400 // The {serialized_as_boilerplate} flag is set when all recursively
401 // reachable JSObjects are serialized.
402 bool serialized_as_boilerplate_ = false;
403 bool serialized_elements_ = false;
404
405 ZoneVector<JSObjectField> inobject_fields_;
406
407 bool serialized_object_create_map_ = false;
408 ObjectData* object_create_map_ = nullptr;
409
410 // Elements (indexed properties) that either
411 // (1) are known to exist directly on the object as non-writable and
412 // non-configurable, or (2) are known not to (possibly they don't exist at
413 // all). In case (2), the second pair component is nullptr.
414 ZoneVector<std::pair<uint32_t, ObjectData*>> own_constant_elements_;
415 // Properties that either:
416 // (1) are known to exist directly on the object, or
417 // (2) are known not to (possibly they don't exist at all).
418 // In case (2), the second pair component is nullptr.
419 // For simplicity, this may in theory overlap with inobject_fields_.
420 // The keys of the map are the property_index() values of the
421 // respective property FieldIndex'es.
422 ZoneUnorderedMap<int, ObjectData*> own_properties_;
423};
424
425void JSObjectData::SerializeObjectCreateMap(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
426 if (serialized_object_create_map_) return;
427 serialized_object_create_map_ = true;
428
429 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "JSObjectData::SerializeObjectCreateMap");
430 Handle<JSObject> jsobject = Handle<JSObject>::cast(object());
431
432 if (jsobject->map().is_prototype_map()) {
433 Handle<Object> maybe_proto_info(jsobject->map().prototype_info(),
434 broker->isolate());
435 if (maybe_proto_info->IsPrototypeInfo()) {
436 auto proto_info = Handle<PrototypeInfo>::cast(maybe_proto_info);
437 if (proto_info->HasObjectCreateMap()) {
438 DCHECK_NULL(object_create_map_)((void) 0);
439 object_create_map_ =
440 broker->GetOrCreateData(proto_info->ObjectCreateMap());
441 }
442 }
443 }
444}
445
446namespace {
447base::Optional<ObjectRef> GetOwnElementFromHeap(JSHeapBroker* broker,
448 Handle<Object> receiver,
449 uint32_t index,
450 bool constant_only) {
451 LookupIterator it(broker->isolate(), receiver, index, LookupIterator::OWN);
452 if (it.state() == LookupIterator::DATA &&
453 (!constant_only || (it.IsReadOnly() && !it.IsConfigurable()))) {
454 return ObjectRef(broker, it.GetDataValue());
455 }
456 return base::nullopt;
457}
458
459ObjectRef GetOwnDataPropertyFromHeap(JSHeapBroker* broker,
460 Handle<JSObject> receiver,
461 Representation representation,
462 FieldIndex field_index) {
463 Handle<Object> constant =
464 JSObject::FastPropertyAt(receiver, representation, field_index);
465 return ObjectRef(broker, constant);
466}
467
468} // namespace
469
470ObjectData* JSObjectData::GetOwnConstantElement(JSHeapBroker* broker,
471 uint32_t index,
472 SerializationPolicy policy) {
473 for (auto const& p : own_constant_elements_) {
474 if (p.first == index) return p.second;
475 }
476
477 if (policy == SerializationPolicy::kAssumeSerialized) {
478 TRACE_MISSING(broker, "knowledge about index " << index << " on " << this);
479 return nullptr;
480 }
481
482 base::Optional<ObjectRef> element =
483 GetOwnElementFromHeap(broker, object(), index, true);
484 ObjectData* result = element.has_value() ? element->data() : nullptr;
485 own_constant_elements_.push_back({index, result});
486 return result;
487}
488
489ObjectData* JSObjectData::GetOwnDataProperty(JSHeapBroker* broker,
490 Representation representation,
491 FieldIndex field_index,
492 SerializationPolicy policy) {
493 auto p = own_properties_.find(field_index.property_index());
494 if (p != own_properties_.end()) return p->second;
495
496 if (policy == SerializationPolicy::kAssumeSerialized) {
497 TRACE_MISSING(broker, "knowledge about property with index "
498 << field_index.property_index() << " on "
499 << this);
500 return nullptr;
501 }
502
503 ObjectRef property = GetOwnDataPropertyFromHeap(
504 broker, Handle<JSObject>::cast(object()), representation, field_index);
505 ObjectData* result(property.data());
506 own_properties_.insert(std::make_pair(field_index.property_index(), result));
507 return result;
508}

694class ContextData : public HeapObjectData {
695 public:
696 ContextData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
697 Handle<Context> object);
698
699 // {previous} will return the closest valid context possible to desired
700 // {depth}, decrementing {depth} for each previous link successfully followed.
701 ContextData* previous(
702 JSHeapBroker* broker, size_t* depth,
703 SerializationPolicy policy = SerializationPolicy::kAssumeSerialized);
704
705 // Returns nullptr if the slot index isn't valid or wasn't serialized,
706 // unless {policy} is {kSerializeIfNeeded}.
707 ObjectData* GetSlot(
708 JSHeapBroker* broker, int index,
709 SerializationPolicy policy = SerializationPolicy::kAssumeSerialized);
710
711 private:
712 ZoneMap<int, ObjectData*> slots_;
713 ContextData* previous_ = nullptr;
714};
715
716ContextData::ContextData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
717 Handle<Context> object)
718 : HeapObjectData(broker, storage, object), slots_(broker->zone()) {}
719
720ContextData* ContextData::previous(JSHeapBroker* broker, size_t* depth,
721 SerializationPolicy policy) {
722 if (*depth == 0) return this;
723
724 if (policy == SerializationPolicy::kSerializeIfNeeded &&
725 previous_ == nullptr) {
726 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "ContextData::previous");
727 Handle<Context> context = Handle<Context>::cast(object());
728 Object prev = context->unchecked_previous();
729 if (prev.IsContext()) {
730 previous_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(prev)->AsContext();
731 }
732 }
733
734 if (previous_ != nullptr) {
735 *depth = *depth - 1;
736 return previous_->previous(broker, depth, policy);
737 }
738 return this;
739}
740
741ObjectData* ContextData::GetSlot(JSHeapBroker* broker, int index,
742 SerializationPolicy policy) {
743 CHECK_GE(index, 0)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpGEImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(index)>::type, typename ::
v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(0)>::type>((index
), (0)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "index" " " ">=" " " "0"); } } while
(false); } while (false);
744 auto search = slots_.find(index);
745 if (search != slots_.end()) {
746 return search->second;
747 }
748
749 if (policy == SerializationPolicy::kSerializeIfNeeded) {
750 Handle<Context> context = Handle<Context>::cast(object());
751 if (index < context->length()) {
752 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "ContextData::GetSlot");
753 TRACE(broker, "Serializing context slot " << index);
754 ObjectData* odata = broker->GetOrCreateData(context->get(index));
755 slots_.insert(std::make_pair(index, odata));
756 return odata;
757 }
758 }
759
760 return nullptr;
761}

799class StringData : public NameData {
800 public:
801 StringData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage, Handle<String> object);
802
803 int length() const { return length_; }
804 uint16_t first_char() const { return first_char_; }
805 base::Optional<double> to_number() const { return to_number_; }
806 bool is_external_string() const { return is_external_string_; }
807 bool is_seq_string() const { return is_seq_string_; }
808
809 StringData* GetCharAsString(
810 JSHeapBroker* broker, uint32_t index,
811 SerializationPolicy policy = SerializationPolicy::kAssumeSerialized);
812
813 private:
814 int const length_;
815 uint16_t const first_char_;
816 base::Optional<double> to_number_;
817 bool const is_external_string_;
818 bool const is_seq_string_;
819
820 // Known individual characters as strings, corresponding to the semantics of
821 // element access (s[i]). The first pair component is always less than
822 // {length_}. The second component is never nullptr.
823 ZoneVector<std::pair<uint32_t, StringData*>> chars_as_strings_;
824
825 static constexpr int kMaxLengthForDoubleConversion = 23;
826};

828class SymbolData : public NameData {
829 public:

831 : NameData(broker, storage, object) {}

833
834StringData::StringData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
835 Handle<String> object)
836 : NameData(broker, storage, object),
837 length_(object->length()),
838 first_char_(length_ > 0 ? object->Get(0) : 0),
839 is_external_string_(object->IsExternalString()),
840 is_seq_string_(object->IsSeqString()),
841 chars_as_strings_(broker->zone()) {
842 if (length_ <= kMaxLengthForDoubleConversion) {
843 const int flags = ALLOW_HEX | ALLOW_OCTAL | ALLOW_BINARY;
844 uc16 buffer[kMaxLengthForDoubleConversion];
845 String::WriteToFlat(*object, buffer, 0, length_);
846 Vector<const uc16> v(buffer, length_);
847 to_number_ = StringToDouble(v, flags);
848 }
849}

851class InternalizedStringData : public StringData {
852 public:
853 InternalizedStringData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
854 Handle<InternalizedString> object);

861
862StringData* StringData::GetCharAsString(JSHeapBroker* broker, uint32_t index,
863 SerializationPolicy policy) {
864 if (index >= static_cast<uint32_t>(length())) return nullptr;
865
866 for (auto const& p : chars_as_strings_) {
867 if (p.first == index) return p.second;
868 }
869
870 if (policy == SerializationPolicy::kAssumeSerialized) {
871 TRACE_MISSING(broker, "knowledge about index " << index << " on " << this);
872 return nullptr;
873 }
874
875 base::Optional<ObjectRef> element =
876 GetOwnElementFromHeap(broker, object(), index, true);
877 StringData* result =
878 element.has_value() ? element->data()->AsString() : nullptr;
879 chars_as_strings_.push_back({index, result});
880 return result;
881}

883InternalizedStringData::InternalizedStringData(
884 JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
885 Handle<InternalizedString> object)
886 : StringData(broker, storage, object) {}
887
888namespace {
889
890bool IsFastLiteralHelper(Handle<JSObject> boilerplate, int max_depth,
891 int* max_properties) {
892 DCHECK_GE(max_depth, 0)((void) 0);
893 DCHECK_GE(*max_properties, 0)((void) 0);
894
895 Isolate* const isolate = boilerplate->GetIsolate();
896
897 // Make sure the boilerplate map is not deprecated.
898 if (!JSObject::TryMigrateInstance(isolate, boilerplate)) return false;
899
900 // Check for too deep nesting.
901 if (max_depth == 0) return false;
902
903 // Check the elements.
904 Handle<FixedArrayBase> elements(boilerplate->elements(), isolate);
905 if (elements->length() > 0 &&
906 elements->map() != ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).fixed_cow_array_map()) {
907 if (boilerplate->HasSmiOrObjectElements()) {
908 Handle<FixedArray> fast_elements = Handle<FixedArray>::cast(elements);
909 int length = elements->length();
910 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
911 if ((*max_properties)-- == 0) return false;
912 Handle<Object> value(fast_elements->get(i), isolate);
913 if (value->IsJSObject()) {
914 Handle<JSObject> value_object = Handle<JSObject>::cast(value);
915 if (!IsFastLiteralHelper(value_object, max_depth - 1,
916 max_properties)) {
917 return false;
918 }
919 }
920 }
921 } else if (boilerplate->HasDoubleElements()) {
922 if (elements->Size() > kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize) return false;
923 } else {
924 return false;
925 }
926 }
927
928 // TODO(turbofan): Do we want to support out-of-object properties?
929 if (!(boilerplate->HasFastProperties() &&
930 boilerplate->property_array().length() == 0)) {
931 return false;
932 }
933
934 // Check the in-object properties.
935 Handle<DescriptorArray> descriptors(boilerplate->map().instance_descriptors(),
936 isolate);
937 for (InternalIndex i : boilerplate->map().IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
938 PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(i);
939 if (details.location() != kField) continue;
940 DCHECK_EQ(kData, details.kind())((void) 0);
941 if ((*max_properties)-- == 0) return false;
942 FieldIndex field_index = FieldIndex::ForDescriptor(boilerplate->map(), i);
943 if (boilerplate->IsUnboxedDoubleField(field_index)) continue;
944 Handle<Object> value(boilerplate->RawFastPropertyAt(field_index), isolate);
945 if (value->IsJSObject()) {
946 Handle<JSObject> value_object = Handle<JSObject>::cast(value);
947 if (!IsFastLiteralHelper(value_object, max_depth - 1, max_properties)) {
948 return false;
949 }
950 }
951 }
952 return true;
953}
954
955// Maximum depth and total number of elements and properties for literal
956// graphs to be considered for fast deep-copying. The limit is chosen to
957// match the maximum number of inobject properties, to ensure that the
958// performance of using object literals is not worse than using constructor
959// functions, see crbug.com/v8/6211 for details.
960const int kMaxFastLiteralDepth = 3;
961const int kMaxFastLiteralProperties = JSObject::kMaxInObjectProperties;
962
963// Determines whether the given array or object literal boilerplate satisfies
964// all limits to be considered for fast deep-copying and computes the total
965// size of all objects that are part of the graph.
966bool IsInlinableFastLiteral(Handle<JSObject> boilerplate) {
967 int max_properties = kMaxFastLiteralProperties;
968 return IsFastLiteralHelper(boilerplate, kMaxFastLiteralDepth,
969 &max_properties);
970}
971
972} // namespace

1165 handle(object->boilerplate(), broker->isolate()));

1168 CanInlineCall_ = object->CanInlineCall();

1171
1172void AllocationSiteData::SerializeBoilerplate(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
1173 if (serialized_boilerplate_) return;
1174 serialized_boilerplate_ = true;
1175
1176 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "AllocationSiteData::SerializeBoilerplate");
1177 Handle<AllocationSite> site = Handle<AllocationSite>::cast(object());
1178
1179 CHECK(IsFastLiteral_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsFastLiteral_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "IsFastLiteral_"); } } while (false);
1180 DCHECK_NULL(boilerplate_)((void) 0);
1181 boilerplate_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(site->boilerplate())->AsJSObject();
1182 boilerplate_->SerializeAsBoilerplate(broker);
1183
1184 DCHECK_NULL(nested_site_)((void) 0);
1185 nested_site_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(site->nested_site());
1186 if (nested_site_->IsAllocationSite()) {
1187 nested_site_->AsAllocationSite()->SerializeBoilerplate(broker);
1188 }
1189}

1191HeapObjectData::HeapObjectData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
1192 Handle<HeapObject> object)
1193 : ObjectData(broker, storage, object, kSerializedHeapObject),
1194 boolean_value_(object->BooleanValue(broker->isolate())),
1195 // We have to use a raw cast below instead of AsMap() because of
1196 // recursion. AsMap() would call IsMap(), which accesses the
1197 // instance_type_ member. In the case of constructing the MapData for the
1198 // meta map (whose map is itself), this member has not yet been
1199 // initialized.
1200 map_(broker->GetOrCreateData(object->map())) {
1201 CHECK(broker->SerializingAllowed())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(broker->SerializingAllowed
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "broker->SerializingAllowed()"
); } } while (false);
1202}
1203
1204InstanceType HeapObjectData::GetMapInstanceType() const {
1205 ObjectData* map_data = map();
1206 if (map_data->should_access_heap()) {
1207 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(kind());
1208 return Handle<Map>::cast(map_data->object())->instance_type();
1209 }
1210 return map_data->AsMap()->instance_type();
1211}
1212
1213namespace {
1214bool IsReadOnlyLengthDescriptor(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Map> jsarray_map) {
1215 DCHECK(!jsarray_map->is_dictionary_map())((void) 0);
1216 Handle<Name> length_string = isolate->factory()->length_string();
1217 DescriptorArray descriptors = jsarray_map->instance_descriptors();
1218 // TODO(jkummerow): We could skip the search and hardcode number == 0.
1219 InternalIndex number = descriptors.Search(*length_string, *jsarray_map);
1220 DCHECK(number.is_found())((void) 0);
1221 return descriptors.GetDetails(number).IsReadOnly();
1222}
1223
1224bool SupportsFastArrayIteration(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Map> map) {
1225 return map->instance_type() == JS_ARRAY_TYPE &&
1226 IsFastElementsKind(map->elements_kind()) &&
1227 map->prototype().IsJSArray() &&
1228 isolate->IsAnyInitialArrayPrototype(
1229 handle(JSArray::cast(map->prototype()), isolate)) &&
1230 Protectors::IsNoElementsIntact(isolate);
1231}
1232
1233bool SupportsFastArrayResize(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Map> map) {
1234 return SupportsFastArrayIteration(isolate, map) && map->is_extensible() &&
1235 !map->is_dictionary_map() && !IsReadOnlyLengthDescriptor(isolate, map);
1236}
1237} // namespace

1239MapData::MapData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage, Handle<Map> object)
1240 : HeapObjectData(broker, storage, object),
1241 instance_type_(object->instance_type()),
1242 instance_size_(object->instance_size()),

1245 bit_field3_(object->bit_field3()),
1246 can_be_deprecated_(object->NumberOfOwnDescriptors() > 0
1247 ? object->CanBeDeprecated()
1248 : false),
1249 can_transition_(object->CanTransition()),
1250 in_object_properties_start_in_words_(
1251 object->IsJSObjectMap() ? object->GetInObjectPropertiesStartInWords()
1252 : 0),
1253 in_object_properties_(
1254 object->IsJSObjectMap() ? object->GetInObjectProperties() : 0),
1255 constructor_function_index_(object->IsPrimitiveMap()
1256 ? object->GetConstructorFunctionIndex()
1257 : Map::kNoConstructorFunctionIndex),
1258 next_free_property_index_(object->NextFreePropertyIndex()),
1259 unused_property_fields_(object->UnusedPropertyFields()),
1260 supports_fast_array_iteration_(
1261 SupportsFastArrayIteration(broker->isolate(), object)),
1262 supports_fast_array_resize_(
1263 SupportsFastArrayResize(broker->isolate(), object)),
1264 is_abandoned_prototype_map_(object->is_abandoned_prototype_map()),
1265 elements_kind_generalizations_(broker->zone()) {}

1267JSFunctionData::JSFunctionData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,

1272 object->has_initial_map()),

1274 has_attached_optimized_code_(object->HasAttachedOptimizedCode()),
1275 PrototypeRequiresRuntimeLookup_(
1276 object->PrototypeRequiresRuntimeLookup()) {}
1277
1278void JSFunctionData::Serialize(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
1279 if (serialized_) return;
1280 serialized_ = true;
1281
1282 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "JSFunctionData::Serialize");
1283 Handle<JSFunction> function = Handle<JSFunction>::cast(object());
1284
1285 DCHECK_NULL(context_)((void) 0);
1286 DCHECK_NULL(native_context_)((void) 0);
1287 DCHECK_NULL(initial_map_)((void) 0);
1288 DCHECK_NULL(prototype_)((void) 0);
1289 DCHECK_NULL(shared_)((void) 0);
1290 DCHECK_NULL(feedback_vector_)((void) 0);
1291 DCHECK_NULL(code_)((void) 0);
1292
1293 context_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(function->context())->AsContext();
1294 native_context_ =
1295 broker->GetOrCreateData(function->native_context())->AsNativeContext();
1296 shared_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(function->shared())->AsSharedFunctionInfo();
1297 feedback_vector_ = has_feedback_vector()
1298 ? broker->GetOrCreateData(function->feedback_vector())
1299 ->AsFeedbackVector()
1300 : nullptr;
1301 code_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(function->code())->AsCode();
1302 initial_map_ = has_initial_map()
1303 ? broker->GetOrCreateData(function->initial_map())->AsMap()
1304 : nullptr;
1305 prototype_ = has_prototype() ? broker->GetOrCreateData(function->prototype())
1306 : nullptr;
1307
1308 if (initial_map_ != nullptr) {
1309 initial_map_instance_size_with_min_slack_ =
1310 function->ComputeInstanceSizeWithMinSlack(broker->isolate());
1311 }
1312 if (initial_map_ != nullptr && !initial_map_->should_access_heap()) {
1313 if (initial_map_->AsMap()->instance_type() == JS_ARRAY_TYPE) {
1314 initial_map_->AsMap()->SerializeElementsKindGeneralizations(broker);
1315 }
1316 initial_map_->AsMap()->SerializeConstructor(broker);
1317 // TODO(neis): This is currently only needed for native_context's
1318 // object_function, as used by GetObjectCreateMap. If no further use sites
1319 // show up, we should move this into NativeContextData::Serialize.
1320 initial_map_->AsMap()->SerializePrototype(broker);
1321 }
1322}
1323
1324void MapData::SerializeElementsKindGeneralizations(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
1325 if (serialized_elements_kind_generalizations_) return;
1326 serialized_elements_kind_generalizations_ = true;
1327
1328 TraceScope tracer(broker, this,
1329 "MapData::SerializeElementsKindGeneralizations");
1330 DCHECK_EQ(instance_type(), JS_ARRAY_TYPE)((void) 0);
1331 MapRef self(broker, this);
1332 ElementsKind from_kind = self.elements_kind();
1333 DCHECK(elements_kind_generalizations_.empty())((void) 0);
1334 for (int i = FIRST_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND; i <= LAST_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND; i++) {
1335 ElementsKind to_kind = static_cast<ElementsKind>(i);
1336 if (IsMoreGeneralElementsKindTransition(from_kind, to_kind)) {
1337 Handle<Map> target =
1338 Map::AsElementsKind(broker->isolate(), self.object(), to_kind);
1339 elements_kind_generalizations_.push_back(
1340 broker->GetOrCreateData(target)->AsMap());
1341 }
1342 }
1343}

("Check failed: %s.", "serialized_"); } } while (false);

1389
1390 private:

1398FeedbackVectorData::FeedbackVectorData(JSHeapBroker* broker,
1399 ObjectData** storage,
1400 Handle<FeedbackVector> object)
1401 : HeapObjectData(broker, storage, object),
1402 invocation_count_(object->invocation_count()),
1403 closure_feedback_cell_array_(broker->zone()) {}
1404
1405FeedbackCellData* FeedbackVectorData::GetClosureFeedbackCell(
1406 JSHeapBroker* broker, int index) const {
1407 CHECK_GE(index, 0)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpGEImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(index)>::type, typename ::
v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(0)>::type>((index
), (0)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "index" " " ">=" " " "0"); } } while
(false); } while (false);
1408
1409 size_t cell_array_size = closure_feedback_cell_array_.size();
1410 if (!serialized_) {
1411 DCHECK_EQ(cell_array_size, 0)((void) 0);
1412 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker,do { if (broker->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker->Trace() << "Missing " << " closure feedback cell array for vector "
<< this << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-heap-broker.cc"
<< ":" << 1413 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
1413 " closure feedback cell array for vector " << this)do { if (broker->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker->Trace() << "Missing " << " closure feedback cell array for vector "
<< this << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-heap-broker.cc"
<< ":" << 1413 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
1414 return nullptr;
1415 }
1416 CHECK_LT(index, cell_array_size)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpLTImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(index)>::type, typename ::
v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(cell_array_size)>::
type>((index), (cell_array_size)); do { if ((__builtin_expect
(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "index" " "
"<" " " "cell_array_size"); } } while (false); } while (false
);
1417 return closure_feedback_cell_array_[index]->AsFeedbackCell();
1418}
1419
1420void FeedbackVectorData::Serialize(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
1421 if (serialized_) return;
1422 serialized_ = true;
1423
1424 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "FeedbackVectorData::Serialize");
1425 Handle<FeedbackVector> vector = Handle<FeedbackVector>::cast(object());
1426 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi(vector->shared_function_info(),
1427 broker->isolate());
1428 shared_function_info_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(sfi)->AsSharedFunctionInfo();
1429 DCHECK(closure_feedback_cell_array_.empty())((void) 0);
1430 int length = vector->closure_feedback_cell_array().length();
1431 closure_feedback_cell_array_.reserve(length);
1432 for (int i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
1433 Handle<FeedbackCell> cell = vector->GetClosureFeedbackCell(i);
1434 ObjectData* cell_data = broker->GetOrCreateData(cell);
1435 closure_feedback_cell_array_.push_back(cell_data);
1436 }
1437 TRACE(broker, "Copied " << length << " feedback cells");
1438}

1473JSBoundFunctionData::JSBoundFunctionData(JSHeapBroker* broker,

1475 Handle<JSBoundFunction> object)
1476 : JSObjectData(broker, storage, object) {}
1477
1478void JSBoundFunctionData::Serialize(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
1479 if (serialized_) return;
1480 serialized_ = true;
1481
1482 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "JSBoundFunctionData::Serialize");
1483 Handle<JSBoundFunction> function = Handle<JSBoundFunction>::cast(object());
1484
1485 DCHECK_NULL(bound_target_function_)((void) 0);
1486 bound_target_function_ =
1487 broker->GetOrCreateData(function->bound_target_function());
1488 if (bound_target_function_->IsJSBoundFunction()) {
1489 bound_target_function_->AsJSBoundFunction()->Serialize(broker);
1490 } else if (bound_target_function_->IsJSFunction()) {
1491 bound_target_function_->AsJSFunction()->Serialize(broker);
1492 }
1493
1494 DCHECK_NULL(bound_arguments_)((void) 0);
1495 bound_arguments_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(function->bound_arguments());
1496 if (!bound_arguments_->should_access_heap()) {
1497 bound_arguments_->AsFixedArray()->SerializeContents(broker);
1498 }
1499
1500 DCHECK_NULL(bound_this_)((void) 0);
1501 bound_this_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(function->bound_this());
1502}

1504JSObjectData::JSObjectData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
1505 Handle<JSObject> object)
1506 : JSReceiverData(broker, storage, object),
1507 inobject_fields_(broker->zone()),
1508 own_constant_elements_(broker->zone()),
1509 own_properties_(broker->zone()) {}

1511FixedArrayData::FixedArrayData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
1512 Handle<FixedArray> object)
1513 : FixedArrayBaseData(broker, storage, object), contents_(broker->zone()) {}
1514
1515void FixedArrayData::SerializeContents(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
1516 if (serialized_contents_) return;
1517 serialized_contents_ = true;
1518
1519 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "FixedArrayData::SerializeContents");
1520 Handle<FixedArray> array = Handle<FixedArray>::cast(object());
1521 CHECK_EQ(array->length(), length())do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(array->length())>::type
, typename ::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(length()
)>::type>((array->length()), (length())); do { if ((
__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s."
, "array->length()" " " "==" " " "length()"); } } while (false
); } while (false);
1522 CHECK(contents_.empty())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(contents_.empty())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "contents_.empty()"); } } while (false);
1523 contents_.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(length()));
1524
1525 for (int i = 0; i < length(); i++) {
1526 Handle<Object> value(array->get(i), broker->isolate());
1527 contents_.push_back(broker->GetOrCreateData(value));
1528 }
1529 TRACE(broker, "Copied " << contents_.size() << " elements");
1530}

1609class JSArrayData : public JSObjectData {
1610 public:
1611 JSArrayData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
1612 Handle<JSArray> object);
1613
1614 void Serialize(JSHeapBroker* broker);
1615 ObjectData* length() const { return length_; }
1616
1617 ObjectData* GetOwnElement(
1618 JSHeapBroker* broker, uint32_t index,
1619 SerializationPolicy policy = SerializationPolicy::kAssumeSerialized);
1620
1621 private:
1622 bool serialized_ = false;
1623 ObjectData* length_ = nullptr;
1624
1625 // Elements (indexed properties) that either
1626 // (1) are known to exist directly on the object, or
1627 // (2) are known not to (possibly they don't exist at all).
1628 // In case (2), the second pair component is nullptr.
1629 ZoneVector<std::pair<uint32_t, ObjectData*>> own_elements_;
1630};
1631
1632JSArrayData::JSArrayData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
1633 Handle<JSArray> object)
1634 : JSObjectData(broker, storage, object), own_elements_(broker->zone()) {}
1635
1636void JSArrayData::Serialize(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
1637 if (serialized_) return;
1638 serialized_ = true;
1639
1640 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "JSArrayData::Serialize");
1641 Handle<JSArray> jsarray = Handle<JSArray>::cast(object());
1642
1643 DCHECK_NULL(length_)((void) 0);
1644 length_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(jsarray->length());
1645}
1646
1647ObjectData* JSArrayData::GetOwnElement(JSHeapBroker* broker, uint32_t index,
1648 SerializationPolicy policy) {
1649 for (auto const& p : own_elements_) {
1650 if (p.first == index) return p.second;
1651 }
1652
1653 if (policy == SerializationPolicy::kAssumeSerialized) {
1654 TRACE_MISSING(broker, "knowledge about index " << index << " on " << this);
1655 return nullptr;
1656 }
1657
1658 base::Optional<ObjectRef> element =
1659 GetOwnElementFromHeap(broker, object(), index, false);
1660 ObjectData* result = element.has_value() ? element->data() : nullptr;
1661 own_elements_.push_back({index, result});
1662 return result;
1663}

1792class SourceTextModuleData : public HeapObjectData {
1793 public:
1794 SourceTextModuleData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
1795 Handle<SourceTextModule> object);
1796 void Serialize(JSHeapBroker* broker);
1797
1798 CellData* GetCell(JSHeapBroker* broker, int cell_index) const;
1799 ObjectData* GetImportMeta(JSHeapBroker* broker) const;
1800
1801 private:
1802 bool serialized_ = false;
1803 ZoneVector<CellData*> imports_;
1804 ZoneVector<CellData*> exports_;
1805 ObjectData* import_meta_;
1806};
1807
1808SourceTextModuleData::SourceTextModuleData(JSHeapBroker* broker,
1809 ObjectData** storage,
1810 Handle<SourceTextModule> object)
1811 : HeapObjectData(broker, storage, object),
1812 imports_(broker->zone()),
1813 exports_(broker->zone()),
1814 import_meta_(nullptr) {}
1815
1816CellData* SourceTextModuleData::GetCell(JSHeapBroker* broker,
1817 int cell_index) const {
1818 if (!serialized_) {
1819 DCHECK(imports_.empty())((void) 0);
1820 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker,do { if (broker->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker->Trace() << "Missing " << "module cell "
<< cell_index << " on " << this << " ("
<< "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-heap-broker.cc" <<
":" << 1821 << ")" << std::endl; } while (
false)
1821 "module cell " << cell_index << " on " << this)do { if (broker->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker->Trace() << "Missing " << "module cell "
<< cell_index << " on " << this << " ("
<< "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-heap-broker.cc" <<
":" << 1821 << ")" << std::endl; } while (
false);
1822 return nullptr;
1823 }
1824 CellData* cell;
1825 switch (SourceTextModuleDescriptor::GetCellIndexKind(cell_index)) {
1826 case SourceTextModuleDescriptor::kImport:
1827 cell = imports_.at(SourceTextModule::ImportIndex(cell_index));
1828 break;
1829 case SourceTextModuleDescriptor::kExport:
1830 cell = exports_.at(SourceTextModule::ExportIndex(cell_index));
1831 break;
1832 case SourceTextModuleDescriptor::kInvalid:
1833 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1834 }
1835 CHECK_NOT_NULL(cell)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!((cell) != nullptr)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "(cell) != nullptr"); } } while (false);
1836 return cell;
1837}
1838
1839ObjectData* SourceTextModuleData::GetImportMeta(JSHeapBroker* broker) const {
1840 CHECK(serialized_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(serialized_)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "serialized_"); } } while (false);
1841 return import_meta_;
1842}
1843
1844void SourceTextModuleData::Serialize(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
1845 if (serialized_) return;
1846 serialized_ = true;
1847
1848 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "SourceTextModuleData::Serialize");
1849 Handle<SourceTextModule> module = Handle<SourceTextModule>::cast(object());
1850
1851 // TODO(neis): We could be smarter and only serialize the cells we care about.
1852 // TODO(neis): Define a helper for serializing a FixedArray into a ZoneVector.
1853
1854 DCHECK(imports_.empty())((void) 0);
1855 Handle<FixedArray> imports(module->regular_imports(), broker->isolate());
1856 int const imports_length = imports->length();
1857 imports_.reserve(imports_length);
1858 for (int i = 0; i < imports_length; ++i) {
1859 imports_.push_back(broker->GetOrCreateData(imports->get(i))->AsCell());
1860 }
1861 TRACE(broker, "Copied " << imports_.size() << " imports");
1862
1863 DCHECK(exports_.empty())((void) 0);
1864 Handle<FixedArray> exports(module->regular_exports(), broker->isolate());
1865 int const exports_length = exports->length();
1866 exports_.reserve(exports_length);
1867 for (int i = 0; i < exports_length; ++i) {
1868 exports_.push_back(broker->GetOrCreateData(exports->get(i))->AsCell());
1869 }
1870 TRACE(broker, "Copied " << exports_.size() << " exports");
1871
1872 DCHECK_NULL(import_meta_)((void) 0);
1873 import_meta_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(module->import_meta());
1874 TRACE(broker, "Copied import_meta");
1875}

1900class JSGlobalObjectData : public JSObjectData {
1901 public:
1902 JSGlobalObjectData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
1903 Handle<JSGlobalObject> object);

1906 PropertyCellData* GetPropertyCell(
1907 JSHeapBroker* broker, NameData* name,
1908 SerializationPolicy policy = SerializationPolicy::kAssumeSerialized);
1909
1910 private:
1911 bool const is_detached_;
1912
1913 // Properties that either
1914 // (1) are known to exist as property cells on the global object, or
1915 // (2) are known not to (possibly they don't exist at all).
1916 // In case (2), the second pair component is nullptr.
1917 ZoneVector<std::pair<NameData*, PropertyCellData*>> properties_;

1927class JSGlobalProxyData : public JSObjectData {
1928 public:
1929 JSGlobalProxyData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
1930 Handle<JSGlobalProxy> object);
1931};
1932
1933JSGlobalProxyData::JSGlobalProxyData(JSHeapBroker* broker, ObjectData** storage,
1934 Handle<JSGlobalProxy> object)
1935 : JSObjectData(broker, storage, object) {}
1936
1937namespace {
1938base::Optional<PropertyCellRef> GetPropertyCellFromHeap(JSHeapBroker* broker,
1939 Handle<Name> name) {
1940 LookupIterator it(
1941 broker->isolate(),
1942 handle(broker->target_native_context().object()->global_object(),
1943 broker->isolate()),
1944 name, LookupIterator::OWN);
1945 it.TryLookupCachedProperty();
1946 if (it.state() == LookupIterator::DATA &&
1947 it.GetHolder<JSObject>()->IsJSGlobalObject()) {
1948 return PropertyCellRef(broker, it.GetPropertyCell());
1949 }
1950 return base::nullopt;
1951}
1952} // namespace
1953
1954PropertyCellData* JSGlobalObjectData::GetPropertyCell(
1955 JSHeapBroker* broker, NameData* name, SerializationPolicy policy) {
1956 CHECK_NOT_NULL(name)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!((name) != nullptr)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "(name) != nullptr"); } } while (false);
1957 for (auto const& p : properties_) {
1958 if (p.first == name) return p.second;
1959 }
1960
1961 if (policy == SerializationPolicy::kAssumeSerialized) {
1962 TRACE_MISSING(broker, "knowledge about global property " << name);
1963 return nullptr;
1964 }
1965
1966 PropertyCellData* result = nullptr;
1967 base::Optional<PropertyCellRef> cell =
1968 GetPropertyCellFromHeap(broker, Handle<Name>::cast(name->object()));
1969 if (cell.has_value()) {
1970 cell->Serialize();
1971 result = cell->data()->AsPropertyCell();
1972 }
1973 properties_.push_back({name, result});
1974 return result;
1975}

1996#define DEFINE_IS_AND_AS(Name) \
1997 bool ObjectData::Is##Name() const { \
1998 if (should_access_heap()) { \
1999 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(kind()); \
2000 return object()->Is##Name(); \
2001 } \
2002 if (is_smi()) return false; \
2003 InstanceType instance_type = \
2004 static_cast<const HeapObjectData*>(this)->GetMapInstanceType(); \
2005 return InstanceTypeChecker::Is##Name(instance_type); \
2006 } \
2007 Name##Data* ObjectData::As##Name() { \
2008 CHECK(Is##Name())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(Is##Name())), 0))) { V8_Fatal

2015 CHECK_LT(static_cast<size_t>(property_index), inobject_fields_.size())do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpLTImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(static_cast<size_t>(property_index
))>::type, typename ::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype
(inobject_fields_.size())>::type>((static_cast<size_t
>(property_index)), (inobject_fields_.size())); do { if ((
__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s."
, "static_cast<size_t>(property_index)" " " "<" " " "inobject_fields_.size()"
); } } while (false); } while (false);
2016 return inobject_fields_[property_index];

2086ObjectData* MapData::GetStrongValue(InternalIndex descriptor_index) const {
2087 auto data = instance_descriptors_->contents().find(descriptor_index.as_int());
2088 if (data == instance_descriptors_->contents().end()) return nullptr;

2092
2093void MapData::SerializeOwnDescriptor(JSHeapBroker* broker,
2094 InternalIndex descriptor_index) {
2095 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "MapData::SerializeOwnDescriptor");
2096 Handle<Map> map = Handle<Map>::cast(object());
2097
2098 if (instance_descriptors_ == nullptr) {
2099 instance_descriptors_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(map->instance_descriptors())
2100 ->AsDescriptorArray();
2101 }
2102
2103 ZoneMap<int, PropertyDescriptor>& contents =
2104 instance_descriptors()->contents();
2105 CHECK_LT(descriptor_index.as_int(), map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors())do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpLTImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(descriptor_index.as_int())>
::type, typename ::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(map
->NumberOfOwnDescriptors())>::type>((descriptor_index
.as_int()), (map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors())); do { if ((__builtin_expect
(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "descriptor_index.as_int()"
" " "<" " " "map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors()"); } } while
(false); } while (false);
2106 if (contents.find(descriptor_index.as_int()) != contents.end()) return;
2107
2108 Isolate* const isolate = broker->isolate();
2109 auto descriptors =
2110 Handle<DescriptorArray>::cast(instance_descriptors_->object());
2111 CHECK_EQ(*descriptors, map->instance_descriptors())do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(*descriptors)>::type, typename
::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(map->instance_descriptors
())>::type>((*descriptors), (map->instance_descriptors
())); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "*descriptors" " " "==" " " "map->instance_descriptors()"
); } } while (false); } while (false);
2112
2113 PropertyDescriptor d;
2114 d.key =
2115 broker->GetOrCreateData(descriptors->GetKey(descriptor_index))->AsName();
2116 MaybeObject value = descriptors->GetValue(descriptor_index);
2117 HeapObject obj;
2118 if (value.GetHeapObjectIfStrong(&obj)) {
2119 d.value = broker->GetOrCreateData(handle(obj, broker->isolate()));
2120 }
2121 d.details = descriptors->GetDetails(descriptor_index);
2122 if (d.details.location() == kField) {
2123 d.field_index = FieldIndex::ForDescriptor(*map, descriptor_index);
2124 d.field_owner =
2125 broker->GetOrCreateData(map->FindFieldOwner(isolate, descriptor_index))
2126 ->AsMap();
2127 d.field_type =
2128 broker->GetOrCreateData(descriptors->GetFieldType(descriptor_index));
2129 d.is_unboxed_double_field = map->IsUnboxedDoubleField(d.field_index);
2130 }
2131 contents[descriptor_index.as_int()] = d;
2132
2133 if (d.details.location() == kField) {
2134 // Recurse on the owner map.
2135 d.field_owner->SerializeOwnDescriptor(broker, descriptor_index);
2136 }
2137
2138 TRACE(broker, "Copied descriptor " << descriptor_index.as_int() << " into "
2139 << instance_descriptors_ << " ("
2140 << contents.size() << " total)");
2141}

2155
2156void JSObjectData::SerializeRecursiveAsBoilerplate(JSHeapBroker* broker,
2157 int depth) {
2158 if (serialized_as_boilerplate_) return;
2159 serialized_as_boilerplate_ = true;
2160
2161 TraceScope tracer(broker, this,
2162 "JSObjectData::SerializeRecursiveAsBoilerplate");
2163 Handle<JSObject> boilerplate = Handle<JSObject>::cast(object());
2164
2165 // We only serialize boilerplates that pass the IsInlinableFastLiteral
2166 // check, so we only do a check on the depth here.
2167 CHECK_GT(depth, 0)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpGTImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(depth)>::type, typename ::
v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(0)>::type>((depth
), (0)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "depth" " " ">" " " "0"); } } while (
false); } while (false);
2168 CHECK(!boilerplate->map().is_deprecated())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!boilerplate->map().is_deprecated
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "!boilerplate->map().is_deprecated()"
); } } while (false);
2169
2170 // Serialize the elements.
2171 Isolate* const isolate = broker->isolate();
2172 Handle<FixedArrayBase> elements_object(boilerplate->elements(), isolate);
2173
2174 // Boilerplates need special serialization - we need to make sure COW arrays
2175 // are tenured. Boilerplate objects should only be reachable from their
2176 // allocation site, so it is safe to assume that the elements have not been
2177 // serialized yet.
2178
2179 bool const empty_or_cow =
2180 elements_object->length() == 0 ||
2181 elements_object->map() == ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).fixed_cow_array_map();
2182 if (empty_or_cow) {
2183 // We need to make sure copy-on-write elements are tenured.
2184 if (ObjectInYoungGeneration(*elements_object)) {
2185 elements_object = isolate->factory()->CopyAndTenureFixedCOWArray(
2186 Handle<FixedArray>::cast(elements_object));
2187 boilerplate->set_elements(*elements_object);
2188 }
2189 cow_or_empty_elements_tenured_ = true;
2190 }
2191
2192 DCHECK_NULL(elements_)((void) 0);
2193 elements_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(elements_object);
2194 DCHECK(elements_->IsFixedArrayBase())((void) 0);
2195
2196 if (empty_or_cow || elements_->should_access_heap()) {
2197 // No need to do anything here. Empty or copy-on-write elements
2198 // do not need to be serialized because we only need to store the elements
2199 // reference to the allocated object.
2200 } else if (boilerplate->HasSmiOrObjectElements()) {
2201 elements_->AsFixedArray()->SerializeContents(broker);
2202 Handle<FixedArray> fast_elements =
2203 Handle<FixedArray>::cast(elements_object);
2204 int length = elements_object->length();
2205 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
2206 Handle<Object> value(fast_elements->get(i), isolate);
2207 if (value->IsJSObject()) {
2208 ObjectData* value_data = broker->GetOrCreateData(value);
2209 value_data->AsJSObject()->SerializeRecursiveAsBoilerplate(broker,
2210 depth - 1);
2211 }
2212 }
2213 } else {
2214 CHECK(boilerplate->HasDoubleElements())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(boilerplate->HasDoubleElements
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "boilerplate->HasDoubleElements()"
); } } while (false);
2215 CHECK_LE(elements_object->Size(), kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpLEImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(elements_object->Size())>
::type, typename ::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize
)>::type>((elements_object->Size()), (kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize
)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s."
, "elements_object->Size()" " " "<=" " " "kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize"
); } } while (false); } while (false);
2216 elements_->AsFixedDoubleArray()->SerializeContents(broker);
2217 }
2218
2219 // TODO(turbofan): Do we want to support out-of-object properties?
2220 CHECK(boilerplate->HasFastProperties() &&do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(boilerplate->HasFastProperties
() && boilerplate->property_array().length() == 0)
), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "boilerplate->HasFastProperties() && boilerplate->property_array().length() == 0"
); } } while (false)
2221 boilerplate->property_array().length() == 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(boilerplate->HasFastProperties
() && boilerplate->property_array().length() == 0)
), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "boilerplate->HasFastProperties() && boilerplate->property_array().length() == 0"
); } } while (false);
2222 CHECK_EQ(inobject_fields_.size(), 0u)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(inobject_fields_.size())>::
type, typename ::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(0u)>
::type>((inobject_fields_.size()), (0u)); do { if ((__builtin_expect
(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "inobject_fields_.size()"
" " "==" " " "0u"); } } while (false); } while (false);
2223
2224 // Check the in-object properties.
2225 Handle<DescriptorArray> descriptors(boilerplate->map().instance_descriptors(),
2226 isolate);
2227 for (InternalIndex i : boilerplate->map().IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
2228 PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(i);
2229 if (details.location() != kField) continue;
2230 DCHECK_EQ(kData, details.kind())((void) 0);
2231
2232 FieldIndex field_index = FieldIndex::ForDescriptor(boilerplate->map(), i);
2233 // Make sure {field_index} agrees with {inobject_properties} on the index of
2234 // this field.
2235 DCHECK_EQ(field_index.property_index(),((void) 0)
2236 static_cast<int>(inobject_fields_.size()))((void) 0);
2237 if (boilerplate->IsUnboxedDoubleField(field_index)) {
2238 uint64_t value_bits =
2239 boilerplate->RawFastDoublePropertyAsBitsAt(field_index);
2240 inobject_fields_.push_back(JSObjectField{value_bits});
2241 } else {
2242 Handle<Object> value(boilerplate->RawFastPropertyAt(field_index),
2243 isolate);
2244 // In case of double fields we use a sentinel NaN value to mark
2245 // uninitialized fields. A boilerplate value with such a field may migrate
2246 // from its double to a tagged representation. If the double is unboxed,
2247 // the raw double is converted to a heap number, otherwise the (boxed)
2248 // double ceases to be mutable, and becomes a normal heap number. The
2249 // sentinel value carries no special meaning when it occurs in a heap
2250 // number, so we would like to recover the uninitialized value. We check
2251 // for the sentinel here, specifically, since migrations might have been
2252 // triggered as part of boilerplate serialization.
2253 if (!details.representation().IsDouble() && value->IsHeapNumber() &&
2254 HeapNumber::cast(*value).value_as_bits() == kHoleNanInt64) {
2255 value = isolate->factory()->uninitialized_value();
2256 }
2257 ObjectData* value_data = broker->GetOrCreateData(value);
2258 if (value->IsJSObject()) {
2259 value_data->AsJSObject()->SerializeRecursiveAsBoilerplate(broker,
2260 depth - 1);
2261 }
2262 inobject_fields_.push_back(JSObjectField{value_data});
2263 }
2264 }
2265 TRACE(broker, "Copied " << inobject_fields_.size() << " in-object fields");
2266
2267 if (!map()->should_access_heap()) {
2268 map()->AsMap()->SerializeOwnDescriptors(broker);
2269 }
2270
2271 if (IsJSArray()) AsJSArray()->Serialize(broker);
2272}

2274void JSRegExpData::SerializeAsRegExpBoilerplate(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
2275 if (serialized_as_reg_exp_boilerplate_) return;
2276 serialized_as_reg_exp_boilerplate_ = true;
2277
2278 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "JSRegExpData::SerializeAsRegExpBoilerplate");
2279 Handle<JSRegExp> boilerplate = Handle<JSRegExp>::cast(object());
2280

2282

2284 broker->GetOrCreateData(boilerplate->raw_properties_or_hash());
2285 data_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(boilerplate->data());

2287 flags_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(boilerplate->flags());
2288 last_index_ = broker->GetOrCreateData(boilerplate->last_index());

2291bool ObjectRef::equals(const ObjectRef& other) const {
2292#ifdef DEBUG
2293 if (broker()->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kSerialized &&
2294 data_->used_status == ObjectData::Usage::kUnused) {
2295 data_->used_status = ObjectData::Usage::kOnlyIdentityUsed;
2296 }
2297#endif // DEBUG
2298 return data_ == other.data_;
2299}
2300
2301Isolate* ObjectRef::isolate() const { return broker()->isolate(); }
2302
2303ContextRef ContextRef::previous(size_t* depth,
2304 SerializationPolicy policy) const {
2305 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(depth)((void) 0);
2306 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
2307 AllowHandleAllocationIf allow_handle_allocation(data()->kind(),
2308 broker()->mode());
2309 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
2310 broker()->mode());
2311 Context current = *object();
2312 while (*depth != 0 && current.unchecked_previous().IsContext()) {
2313 current = Context::cast(current.unchecked_previous());
2314 (*depth)--;
2315 }
2316 return ContextRef(broker(), handle(current, broker()->isolate()));
2317 }
2318 ContextData* current = this->data()->AsContext();
2319 return ContextRef(broker(), current->previous(broker(), depth, policy));
2320}
2321
2322base::Optional<ObjectRef> ContextRef::get(int index,
2323 SerializationPolicy policy) const {
2324 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
2325 AllowHandleAllocationIf allow_handle_allocation(data()->kind(),
2326 broker()->mode());
2327 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
2328 broker()->mode());
2329 Handle<Object> value(object()->get(index), broker()->isolate());
2330 return ObjectRef(broker(), value);
2331 }
2332 ObjectData* optional_slot =
2333 data()->AsContext()->GetSlot(broker(), index, policy);
2334 if (optional_slot != nullptr) {
2335 return ObjectRef(broker(), optional_slot);
2336 }
2337 return base::nullopt;
2338}
2339
2340SourceTextModuleRef ContextRef::GetModule(SerializationPolicy policy) const {
2341 ContextRef current = *this;
2342 while (current.map().instance_type() != MODULE_CONTEXT_TYPE) {
2343 size_t depth = 1;
2344 current = current.previous(&depth, policy);
2345 CHECK_EQ(depth, 0)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(depth)>::type, typename ::
v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(0)>::type>((depth
), (0)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "depth" " " "==" " " "0"); } } while (false
); } while (false);
2346 }
2347 return current.get(Context::EXTENSION_INDEX, policy)
2348 .value()
2349 .AsSourceTextModule();
2350}
2351
2352JSHeapBroker::JSHeapBroker(Isolate* isolate, Zone* broker_zone,
2353 bool tracing_enabled, bool is_concurrent_inlining,
2354 bool is_native_context_independent)
2355 : isolate_(isolate),
2356 zone_(broker_zone),
2357 refs_(zone()->New<RefsMap>(kMinimalRefsBucketCount, AddressMatcher(),
2358 zone())),
2359 root_index_map_(isolate),
2360 array_and_object_prototypes_(zone()),
2361 tracing_enabled_(tracing_enabled),
2362 is_concurrent_inlining_(is_concurrent_inlining),
2363 is_native_context_independent_(is_native_context_independent),
2364 local_heap_(base::nullopt),
2365 feedback_(zone()),
2366 bytecode_analyses_(zone()),
2367 property_access_infos_(zone()),
2368 minimorphic_property_access_infos_(zone()),
2369 typed_array_string_tags_(zone()),
2370 serialized_functions_(zone()) {
2371 // Note that this initialization of {refs_} with the minimal initial capacity
2372 // is redundant in the normal use case (concurrent compilation enabled,
2373 // standard objects to be serialized), as the map is going to be replaced
2374 // immediately with a larger-capacity one. It doesn't seem to affect the
2375 // performance in a noticeable way though.
2376 TRACE(this, "Constructing heap broker");
2377}
2378
2379JSHeapBroker::~JSHeapBroker() { DCHECK(!local_heap_)((void) 0); }
2380
2381void JSHeapBroker::SetPersistentAndCopyCanonicalHandlesForTesting(
2382 std::unique_ptr<PersistentHandles> persistent_handles,
2383 std::unique_ptr<CanonicalHandlesMap> canonical_handles) {
2384 set_persistent_handles(std::move(persistent_handles));
2385 CopyCanonicalHandlesForTesting(std::move(canonical_handles));
2386}
2387
2388void JSHeapBroker::CopyCanonicalHandlesForTesting(
2389 std::unique_ptr<CanonicalHandlesMap> canonical_handles) {
2390 DCHECK_NULL(canonical_handles_)((void) 0);
2391 canonical_handles_ = std::make_unique<CanonicalHandlesMap>(
2392 isolate_->heap(), ZoneAllocationPolicy(zone()));
2393
2394 CanonicalHandlesMap::IteratableScope it_scope(canonical_handles.get());
2395 for (auto it = it_scope.begin(); it != it_scope.end(); ++it) {
2396 Address* entry = *it.entry();
2397 Object key = it.key();
2398 canonical_handles_->Set(key, entry);
2399 }
2400}
2401
2402std::string JSHeapBroker::Trace() const {
2403 std::ostringstream oss;
2404 oss << "[" << this << "] ";
2405 for (unsigned i = 0; i < trace_indentation_ * 2; ++i) oss.put(' ');
2406 return oss.str();
2407}
2408
2409void JSHeapBroker::InitializeLocalHeap(OptimizedCompilationInfo* info) {
2410 set_persistent_handles(info->DetachPersistentHandles());
2411 set_canonical_handles(info->DetachCanonicalHandles());
2412 DCHECK(!local_heap_)((void) 0);
2413 local_heap_.emplace(isolate_->heap(), std::move(ph_));
2414}
2415
2416void JSHeapBroker::TearDownLocalHeap(OptimizedCompilationInfo* info) {
2417 DCHECK_NULL(ph_)((void) 0);
2418 DCHECK(local_heap_)((void) 0);
2419 ph_ = local_heap_->DetachPersistentHandles();
2420 local_heap_.reset();
2421 info->set_canonical_handles(DetachCanonicalHandles());
2422 info->set_persistent_handles(DetachPersistentHandles());
2423}
2424
2425void JSHeapBroker::StopSerializing() {
2426 CHECK_EQ(mode_, kSerializing)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(mode_)>::type, typename ::
v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(kSerializing)>::type
>((mode_), (kSerializing)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(
!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "mode_" " " "=="
" " "kSerializing"); } } while (false); } while (false);
2427 TRACE(this, "Stopping serialization");
2428 mode_ = kSerialized;
2429}

2431#ifdef DEBUG
2432void JSHeapBroker::PrintRefsAnalysis() const {
2433 // Usage counts
2434 size_t used_total = 0, unused_total = 0, identity_used_total = 0;
2435 for (RefsMap::Entry* ref = refs_->Start(); ref != nullptr;
2436 ref = refs_->Next(ref)) {
2437 switch (ref->value->used_status) {
2438 case ObjectData::Usage::kUnused:
2439 ++unused_total;
2440 break;
2441 case ObjectData::Usage::kOnlyIdentityUsed:
2442 ++identity_used_total;
2443 break;
2444 case ObjectData::Usage::kDataUsed:
2445 ++used_total;
2446 break;
2447 }
2448 }
2449
2450 // Ref types analysis
2451 TRACE_BROKER_MEMORY(do { if (this->tracing_enabled() && FLAG_trace_heap_broker_memory
) StdoutStream{} << this->Trace() << "Refs: " <<
refs_->occupancy() << "; data used: " << used_total
<< "; only identity used: " << identity_used_total
<< "; unused: " << unused_total << std::endl
; } while (false)
2452 this, "Refs: " << refs_->occupancy() << "; data used: " << used_totaldo { if (this->tracing_enabled() && FLAG_trace_heap_broker_memory
) StdoutStream{} << this->Trace() << "Refs: " <<
refs_->occupancy() << "; data used: " << used_total
<< "; only identity used: " << identity_used_total
<< "; unused: " << unused_total << std::endl
; } while (false)
2453 << "; only identity used: " << identity_used_totaldo { if (this->tracing_enabled() && FLAG_trace_heap_broker_memory
) StdoutStream{} << this->Trace() << "Refs: " <<
refs_->occupancy() << "; data used: " << used_total
<< "; only identity used: " << identity_used_total
<< "; unused: " << unused_total << std::endl
; } while (false)
2454 << "; unused: " << unused_total)do { if (this->tracing_enabled() && FLAG_trace_heap_broker_memory
) StdoutStream{} << this->Trace() << "Refs: " <<
refs_->occupancy() << "; data used: " << used_total
<< "; only identity used: " << identity_used_total
<< "; unused: " << unused_total << std::endl
; } while (false);
2455 size_t used_smis = 0, unused_smis = 0, identity_used_smis = 0;
2456 size_t used[LAST_TYPE + 1] = {0};
2457 size_t unused[LAST_TYPE + 1] = {0};
2458 size_t identity_used[LAST_TYPE + 1] = {0};
2459 for (RefsMap::Entry* ref = refs_->Start(); ref != nullptr;
2460 ref = refs_->Next(ref)) {
2461 if (ref->value->is_smi()) {
2462 switch (ref->value->used_status) {
2463 case ObjectData::Usage::kUnused:
2464 ++unused_smis;
2465 break;
2466 case ObjectData::Usage::kOnlyIdentityUsed:
2467 ++identity_used_smis;
2468 break;
2469 case ObjectData::Usage::kDataUsed:
2470 ++used_smis;
2471 break;
2472 }
2473 } else {
2474 InstanceType instance_type;
2475 if (ref->value->should_access_heap()) {
2476 instance_type = Handle<HeapObject>::cast(ref->value->object())
2477 ->map()
2478 .instance_type();
2479 } else {
2480 instance_type = ref->value->AsHeapObject()->GetMapInstanceType();
2481 }
2482 CHECK_LE(FIRST_TYPE, instance_type)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpLEImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(FIRST_TYPE)>::type, typename
::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(instance_type)>
::type>((FIRST_TYPE), (instance_type)); do { if ((__builtin_expect
(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "FIRST_TYPE"
" " "<=" " " "instance_type"); } } while (false); } while
(false);
2483 CHECK_LE(instance_type, LAST_TYPE)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpLEImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(instance_type)>::type, typename
::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(LAST_TYPE)>::type
>((instance_type), (LAST_TYPE)); do { if ((__builtin_expect
(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "instance_type"
" " "<=" " " "LAST_TYPE"); } } while (false); } while (false
);
2484 switch (ref->value->used_status) {
2485 case ObjectData::Usage::kUnused:
2486 ++unused[instance_type];
2487 break;
2488 case ObjectData::Usage::kOnlyIdentityUsed:
2489 ++identity_used[instance_type];
2490 break;
2491 case ObjectData::Usage::kDataUsed:
2492 ++used[instance_type];
2493 break;
2494 }
2495 }
2496 }
2497
2498 TRACE_BROKER_MEMORY(do { if (this->tracing_enabled() && FLAG_trace_heap_broker_memory
) StdoutStream{} << this->Trace() << "Smis: " <<
used_smis + identity_used_smis + unused_smis << "; data used: "
<< used_smis << "; only identity used: " <<
identity_used_smis << "; unused: " << unused_smis
<< std::endl; } while (false)
2499 this, "Smis: " << used_smis + identity_used_smis + unused_smisdo { if (this->tracing_enabled() && FLAG_trace_heap_broker_memory
) StdoutStream{} << this->Trace() << "Smis: " <<
used_smis + identity_used_smis + unused_smis << "; data used: "
<< used_smis << "; only identity used: " <<
identity_used_smis << "; unused: " << unused_smis
<< std::endl; } while (false)
2500 << "; data used: " << used_smis << "; only identity used: "do { if (this->tracing_enabled() && FLAG_trace_heap_broker_memory
) StdoutStream{} << this->Trace() << "Smis: " <<
used_smis + identity_used_smis + unused_smis << "; data used: "
<< used_smis << "; only identity used: " <<
identity_used_smis << "; unused: " << unused_smis
<< std::endl; } while (false)
2501 << identity_used_smis << "; unused: " << unused_smis)do { if (this->tracing_enabled() && FLAG_trace_heap_broker_memory
) StdoutStream{} << this->Trace() << "Smis: " <<
used_smis + identity_used_smis + unused_smis << "; data used: "
<< used_smis << "; only identity used: " <<
identity_used_smis << "; unused: " << unused_smis
<< std::endl; } while (false);
2502 for (uint16_t i = FIRST_TYPE; i <= LAST_TYPE; ++i) {
2503 size_t total = used[i] + identity_used[i] + unused[i];
2504 if (total == 0) continue;
2505 TRACE_BROKER_MEMORY(do { if (this->tracing_enabled() && FLAG_trace_heap_broker_memory
) StdoutStream{} << this->Trace() << InstanceType
(i) << ": " << total << "; data used: " <<
used[i] << "; only identity used: " << identity_used
[i] << "; unused: " << unused[i] << std::endl
; } while (false)
2506 this, InstanceType(i) << ": " << total << "; data used: " << used[i]do { if (this->tracing_enabled() && FLAG_trace_heap_broker_memory
) StdoutStream{} << this->Trace() << InstanceType
(i) << ": " << total << "; data used: " <<
used[i] << "; only identity used: " << identity_used
[i] << "; unused: " << unused[i] << std::endl
; } while (false)
2507 << "; only identity used: " << identity_used[i]do { if (this->tracing_enabled() && FLAG_trace_heap_broker_memory
) StdoutStream{} << this->Trace() << InstanceType
(i) << ": " << total << "; data used: " <<
used[i] << "; only identity used: " << identity_used
[i] << "; unused: " << unused[i] << std::endl
; } while (false)
2508 << "; unused: " << unused[i])do { if (this->tracing_enabled() && FLAG_trace_heap_broker_memory
) StdoutStream{} << this->Trace() << InstanceType
(i) << ": " << total << "; data used: " <<
used[i] << "; only identity used: " << identity_used

2513void JSHeapBroker::Retire() {
2514 CHECK_EQ(mode_, kSerialized)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(mode_)>::type, typename ::
v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(kSerialized)>::type
>((mode_), (kSerialized)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!
(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "mode_" " " "=="
" " "kSerialized"); } } while (false); } while (false);
2515 TRACE(this, "Retiring");
2516 mode_ = kRetired;

2523bool JSHeapBroker::SerializingAllowed() const { return mode() == kSerializing; }
2524
2525void JSHeapBroker::SetTargetNativeContextRef(
2526 Handle<NativeContext> native_context) {
2527 // The MapData constructor uses {target_native_context_}. This creates a
2528 // benign cycle that we break by setting {target_native_context_} right before
2529 // starting to serialize (thus creating dummy data), and then again properly
2530 // right after.
2531 DCHECK((mode() == kDisabled && !target_native_context_.has_value()) ||((void) 0)
2532 (mode() == kSerializing &&((void) 0)
2533 target_native_context_->object().equals(native_context) &&((void) 0)
2534 target_native_context_->data_->kind() == kUnserializedHeapObject))((void) 0);
2535 target_native_context_ = NativeContextRef(this, native_context);
2536}
2537
2538void JSHeapBroker::CollectArrayAndObjectPrototypes() {
2539 DisallowHeapAllocation no_gc;
2540 CHECK_EQ(mode(), kSerializing)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(mode())>::type, typename ::
v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(kSerializing)>::type
>((mode()), (kSerializing)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!
(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "mode()" " " "=="
" " "kSerializing"); } } while (false); } while (false);
2541 CHECK(array_and_object_prototypes_.empty())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(array_and_object_prototypes_.
empty())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "array_and_object_prototypes_.empty()"
); } } while (false);
2542
2543 Object maybe_context = isolate()->heap()->native_contexts_list();
2544 while (!maybe_context.IsUndefined(isolate())) {
2545 Context context = Context::cast(maybe_context);
2546 Object array_prot = context.get(Context::INITIAL_ARRAY_PROTOTYPE_INDEX);
2547 Object object_prot = context.get(Context::INITIAL_OBJECT_PROTOTYPE_INDEX);
2548 array_and_object_prototypes_.emplace(JSObject::cast(array_prot), isolate());
2549 array_and_object_prototypes_.emplace(JSObject::cast(object_prot),
2550 isolate());
2551 maybe_context = context.next_context_link();
2552 }
2553
2554 CHECK(!array_and_object_prototypes_.empty())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!array_and_object_prototypes_
.empty())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "!array_and_object_prototypes_.empty()"
); } } while (false);
2555}

2570bool JSHeapBroker::ShouldBeSerializedForCompilation(
2571 const SharedFunctionInfoRef& shared, const FeedbackVectorRef& feedback,
2572 const HintsVector& arguments) const {
2573 if (serialized_functions_.size() >= kMaxSerializedFunctionsCacheSize) {
2574 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(this,do { if (this->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} << this
->Trace() << "Missing " << "opportunity - serialized functions cache is full."
<< " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-heap-broker.cc"
<< ":" << 2575 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
2575 "opportunity - serialized functions cache is full.")do { if (this->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} << this
->Trace() << "Missing " << "opportunity - serialized functions cache is full."
<< " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-heap-broker.cc"
<< ":" << 2575 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
2576 return false;
2577 }
2578 SerializedFunction function{shared, feedback};
2579 auto matching_functions = serialized_functions_.equal_range(function);
2580 return std::find_if(matching_functions.first, matching_functions.second,
2581 [&arguments](const auto& entry) {
2582 return entry.second == arguments;
2583 }) == matching_functions.second;
2584}
2585
2586void JSHeapBroker::SetSerializedForCompilation(
2587 const SharedFunctionInfoRef& shared, const FeedbackVectorRef& feedback,
2588 const HintsVector& arguments) {
2589 SerializedFunction function{shared, feedback};
2590 serialized_functions_.insert({function, arguments});
2591 TRACE(this, "Set function " << shared << " with " << feedback
2592 << " as serialized for compilation");
2593}
2594
2595bool JSHeapBroker::IsSerializedForCompilation(
2596 const SharedFunctionInfoRef& shared,
2597 const FeedbackVectorRef& feedback) const {
2598 if (mode() == kDisabled) return true;
2599
2600 SerializedFunction function = {shared, feedback};
2601 return serialized_functions_.find(function) != serialized_functions_.end();
2602}
2603
2604bool JSHeapBroker::IsArrayOrObjectPrototype(const JSObjectRef& object) const {
2605 if (mode() == kDisabled) {
2606 return isolate()->IsInAnyContext(*object.object(),
2607 Context::INITIAL_ARRAY_PROTOTYPE_INDEX) ||
2608 isolate()->IsInAnyContext(*object.object(),
2609 Context::INITIAL_OBJECT_PROTOTYPE_INDEX);
2610 }
2611 CHECK(!array_and_object_prototypes_.empty())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!array_and_object_prototypes_
.empty())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "!array_and_object_prototypes_.empty()"
); } } while (false);
2612 return array_and_object_prototypes_.find(object.object()) !=
2613 array_and_object_prototypes_.end();
2614}
2615
2616void JSHeapBroker::InitializeAndStartSerializing(
2617 Handle<NativeContext> native_context) {
2618 TraceScope tracer(this, "JSHeapBroker::InitializeAndStartSerializing");
2619
2620 CHECK_EQ(mode_, kDisabled)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(mode_)>::type, typename ::
v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(kDisabled)>::type>
((mode_), (kDisabled)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)
), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "mode_" " " "==" " " "kDisabled"
); } } while (false); } while (false);
2621 mode_ = kSerializing;
2622
2623 // Throw away the dummy data that we created while disabled.
2624 refs_->Clear();
2625 refs_ = nullptr;
2626
2627 refs_ =
2628 zone()->New<RefsMap>(kInitialRefsBucketCount, AddressMatcher(), zone());
2629
2630 SetTargetNativeContextRef(native_context);
2631 target_native_context().Serialize();
2632
2633 CollectArrayAndObjectPrototypes();
2634
2635 // Serialize Cells
2636 Factory* const f = isolate()->factory();
2637 GetOrCreateData(f->array_buffer_detaching_protector())
2638 ->AsPropertyCell()
2639 ->Serialize(this);
2640 GetOrCreateData(f->array_constructor_protector())
2641 ->AsPropertyCell()
2642 ->Serialize(this);
2643 GetOrCreateData(f->array_iterator_protector())
2644 ->AsPropertyCell()
2645 ->Serialize(this);
2646 GetOrCreateData(f->array_species_protector())
2647 ->AsPropertyCell()
2648 ->Serialize(this);
2649 GetOrCreateData(f->many_closures_cell())->AsFeedbackCell();
2650 GetOrCreateData(f->no_elements_protector())
2651 ->AsPropertyCell()
2652 ->Serialize(this);
2653 GetOrCreateData(f->promise_hook_protector())
2654 ->AsPropertyCell()
2655 ->Serialize(this);
2656 GetOrCreateData(f->promise_species_protector())
2657 ->AsPropertyCell()
2658 ->Serialize(this);
2659 GetOrCreateData(f->promise_then_protector())
2660 ->AsPropertyCell()
2661 ->Serialize(this);
2662 GetOrCreateData(f->string_length_protector())
2663 ->AsPropertyCell()
2664 ->Serialize(this);
2665 // - CEntry stub
2666 GetOrCreateData(
2667 CodeFactory::CEntry(isolate(), 1, kDontSaveFPRegs, kArgvOnStack, true));
2668
2669 TRACE(this, "Finished serializing standard objects");
2670}

2672// clang-format off
2673ObjectData* JSHeapBroker::GetOrCreateData(Handle<Object> object) {
2674 RefsMap::Entry* entry = refs_->LookupOrInsert(object.address());
2675 ObjectData* object_data = entry->value;
2676
2677 if (object_data == nullptr) {
2678 ObjectData** data_storage = &(entry->value);
2679 // TODO(neis): Remove these Allow* once we serialize everything upfront.
2680 AllowHandleDereference handle_dereference;
2681 if (object->IsSmi()) {
2682 object_data = zone()->New<ObjectData>(this, data_storage, object, kSmi);
2683 } else if (IsReadOnlyHeapObject(*object)) {
2684 object_data = zone()->New<ObjectData>(this, data_storage, object,
2685 kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject);
2686#define CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(name) \
2687 } else if (object->Is##name()) { \
2688 CHECK(SerializingAllowed())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(SerializingAllowed())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "SerializingAllowed()"); } } while
(false); \
2689 AllowHandleAllocation handle_allocation; \
2690 object_data = zone()->New<name##Data>(this, data_storage, \
2691 Handle<name>::cast(object));
2692
2693 HEAP_BROKER_OBJECT_LIST(CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH)CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(JSArray) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(JSBoundFunction
) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(JSDataView) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(JSFunction
) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(JSGlobalObject) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(JSGlobalProxy
) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(JSRegExp) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(JSTypedArray
) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(NativeContext) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(Context
) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(ObjectBoilerplateDescription) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH
(ScopeInfo) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(ScriptContextTable) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH
(BytecodeArray) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(FixedArray) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH
(FixedDoubleArray) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(InternalizedString) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH
(String) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(Symbol) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(JSObject
) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(AccessorInfo) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(AllocationSite
) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(ArrayBoilerplateDescription) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH
(BigInt) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(CallHandlerInfo) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH
(Cell) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(Code) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(DescriptorArray
) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(FeedbackCell) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(FeedbackVector
) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(FixedArrayBase) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(FunctionTemplateInfo
) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(HeapNumber) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(JSReceiver
) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(Map) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(Name) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH
(PropertyCell) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(SharedFunctionInfo) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH
(SourceTextModule) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(TemplateObjectDescription
) CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH(HeapObject)
2694#undef CREATE_DATA_IF_MATCH
2695 } else {
2696 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
2697 }
2698 // At this point the entry pointer is not guaranteed to be valid as
2699 // the refs_ hash hable could be resized by one of the constructors above.
2700 DCHECK_EQ(object_data, refs_->Lookup(object.address())->value)((void) 0);
2701 }
2702 return object_data;
2703}

2721int ObjectRef::AsSmi() const {

2726
2727base::Optional<MapRef> JSObjectRef::GetObjectCreateMap() const {
2728 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
2729 DCHECK(data_->kind() != ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)((void) 0);
2730 AllowHandleAllocationIf allow_handle_allocation(data()->kind(),
2731 broker()->mode());
2732 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
2733 broker()->mode());
2734 AllowHeapAllocationIf allow_heap_allocation(data()->kind(),
2735 broker()->mode());
2736 Handle<Map> instance_map;
2737 if (Map::TryGetObjectCreateMap(broker()->isolate(), object())
2738 .ToHandle(&instance_map)) {
2739 return MapRef(broker(), instance_map);
2740 } else {
2741 return base::Optional<MapRef>();
2742 }
2743 }
2744 ObjectData* map_data = data()->AsJSObject()->object_create_map(broker());
2745 if (map_data == nullptr) return base::Optional<MapRef>();
2746 if (map_data->should_access_heap()) {
2747 return MapRef(broker(), map_data->object());
2748 }
2749 return MapRef(broker(), map_data->AsMap());
2750}
