2752#define DEF_TESTER(Type, ...) \
2753 bool MapRef::Is##Type##Map() const { \
2754 return InstanceTypeChecker::Is##Type(instance_type()); \
2755 }

2759base::Optional<MapRef> MapRef::AsElementsKind(ElementsKind kind) const {
2760 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
2761 AllowHandleAllocationIf allow_handle_allocation(data()->kind(),
2762 broker()->mode());
2763 AllowHeapAllocationIf allow_heap_allocation(data()->kind(),
2764 broker()->mode());
2765 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
2766 broker()->mode());
2767 return MapRef(broker(),
2768 Map::AsElementsKind(broker()->isolate(), object(), kind));
2769 }
2770 if (kind == elements_kind()) return *this;
2771 const ZoneVector<MapData*>& elements_kind_generalizations =
2772 data()->AsMap()->elements_kind_generalizations();
2773 for (auto data : elements_kind_generalizations) {
2774 MapRef map(broker(), data);
2775 if (map.elements_kind() == kind) return map;
2776 }
2777 return base::Optional<MapRef>();
2778}
2779
2780void MapRef::SerializeForElementLoad() {
2781 CHECK_EQ(broker()->mode(), JSHeapBroker::kSerializing)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(broker()->mode())>::type
, typename ::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(JSHeapBroker
::kSerializing)>::type>((broker()->mode()), (JSHeapBroker
::kSerializing)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))
) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "broker()->mode()" " " "=="
" " "JSHeapBroker::kSerializing"); } } while (false); } while
(false);
2782 if (data()->kind() == ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject) return;
2783 data()->AsMap()->SerializeForElementLoad(broker());
2784}
2785
2786void MapRef::SerializeForElementStore() {
2787 CHECK_EQ(broker()->mode(), JSHeapBroker::kSerializing)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(broker()->mode())>::type
, typename ::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(JSHeapBroker
::kSerializing)>::type>((broker()->mode()), (JSHeapBroker
::kSerializing)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))
) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "broker()->mode()" " " "=="
" " "JSHeapBroker::kSerializing"); } } while (false); } while
(false);
2788 if (data()->kind() == ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject) return;
2789 data()->AsMap()->SerializeForElementStore(broker());
2790}
2791
2792namespace {
2793// This helper function has two modes. If {prototype_maps} is nullptr, the
2794// prototype chain is serialized as necessary to determine the result.
2795// Otherwise, the heap is untouched and the encountered prototypes are pushed
2796// onto {prototype_maps}.
2797bool HasOnlyStablePrototypesWithFastElementsHelper(
2798 JSHeapBroker* broker, MapRef const& map,
2799 ZoneVector<MapRef>* prototype_maps) {
2800 for (MapRef prototype_map = map;;) {
2801 if (prototype_maps == nullptr) prototype_map.SerializePrototype();
2802 prototype_map = prototype_map.prototype().AsHeapObject().map();
2803 if (prototype_map.oddball_type() == OddballType::kNull) return true;
2804 if (!map.prototype().IsJSObject() || !prototype_map.is_stable() ||
2805 !IsFastElementsKind(prototype_map.elements_kind())) {
2806 return false;
2807 }
2808 if (prototype_maps != nullptr) prototype_maps->push_back(prototype_map);
2809 }
2810}
2811} // namespace
2812
2813void MapData::SerializeForElementLoad(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
2814 if (serialized_for_element_load_) return;
2815 serialized_for_element_load_ = true;
2816
2817 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "MapData::SerializeForElementLoad");
2818 SerializePrototype(broker);
2819}
2820
2821void MapData::SerializeForElementStore(JSHeapBroker* broker) {
2822 if (serialized_for_element_store_) return;
2823 serialized_for_element_store_ = true;
2824
2825 TraceScope tracer(broker, this, "MapData::SerializeForElementStore");
2826 HasOnlyStablePrototypesWithFastElementsHelper(broker, MapRef(broker, this),
2827 nullptr);
2828}
2829
2830bool MapRef::HasOnlyStablePrototypesWithFastElements(
2831 ZoneVector<MapRef>* prototype_maps) {
2832 for (MapRef prototype_map = *this;;) {
2833 if (prototype_maps == nullptr) prototype_map.SerializePrototype();
2834 prototype_map = prototype_map.prototype().AsHeapObject().map();
2835 if (prototype_map.oddball_type() == OddballType::kNull) return true;
2836 if (!prototype().IsJSObject() || !prototype_map.is_stable() ||
2837 !IsFastElementsKind(prototype_map.elements_kind())) {
2838 return false;
2839 }
2840 if (prototype_maps != nullptr) prototype_maps->push_back(prototype_map);
2841 }
2842}
2843
2844bool MapRef::supports_fast_array_iteration() const {
2845 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
2846 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
2847 broker()->mode());
2848 AllowHandleAllocationIf allow_handle_allocation(data()->kind(),
2849 broker()->mode());
2850 return SupportsFastArrayIteration(broker()->isolate(), object());
2851 }
2852 return data()->AsMap()->supports_fast_array_iteration();
2853}

2855bool MapRef::supports_fast_array_resize() const {
2856 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
2857 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
2858 broker()->mode());
2859 AllowHandleAllocationIf allow_handle_allocation(data()->kind(),
2860 broker()->mode());
2861 return SupportsFastArrayResize(broker()->isolate(), object());
2862 }
2863 return data()->AsMap()->supports_fast_array_resize();
2864}
2865
2866int JSFunctionRef::InitialMapInstanceSizeWithMinSlack() const {
2867 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
2868 DCHECK(data_->kind() != ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)((void) 0);
2869 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
2870 broker()->mode());
2871 AllowHandleAllocationIf allow_handle_allocation(data()->kind(),
2872 broker()->mode());
2873 return object()->ComputeInstanceSizeWithMinSlack(broker()->isolate());
2874 }
2875 return data()->AsJSFunction()->initial_map_instance_size_with_min_slack();
2876}
2877
2878OddballType MapRef::oddball_type() const {
2879 if (instance_type() != ODDBALL_TYPE) {
2880 return OddballType::kNone;
2881 }
2882 Factory* f = broker()->isolate()->factory();
2883 if (equals(MapRef(broker(), f->undefined_map()))) {
2884 return OddballType::kUndefined;
2885 }
2886 if (equals(MapRef(broker(), f->null_map()))) {
2887 return OddballType::kNull;
2888 }
2889 if (equals(MapRef(broker(), f->boolean_map()))) {
2890 return OddballType::kBoolean;
2891 }
2892 if (equals(MapRef(broker(), f->the_hole_map()))) {
2893 return OddballType::kHole;
2894 }
2895 if (equals(MapRef(broker(), f->uninitialized_map()))) {
2896 return OddballType::kUninitialized;
2897 }
2898 DCHECK(equals(MapRef(broker(), f->termination_exception_map())) ||((void) 0)
2899 equals(MapRef(broker(), f->arguments_marker_map())) ||((void) 0)
2900 equals(MapRef(broker(), f->optimized_out_map())) ||((void) 0)
2901 equals(MapRef(broker(), f->stale_register_map())))((void) 0);
2902 return OddballType::kOther;
2903}
2904
2905FeedbackCellRef FeedbackVectorRef::GetClosureFeedbackCell(int index) const {
2906 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
2907 DCHECK(data_->kind() != ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)((void) 0);
2908 AllowHandleAllocationIf allow_handle_allocation(data()->kind(),
2909 broker()->mode());
2910 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
2911 broker()->mode());
2912 return FeedbackCellRef(broker(), object()->GetClosureFeedbackCell(index));
2913 }
2914
2915 return FeedbackCellRef(
2916 broker(),
2917 data()->AsFeedbackVector()->GetClosureFeedbackCell(broker(), index));
2918}
2919
2920double JSObjectRef::RawFastDoublePropertyAt(FieldIndex index) const {
2921 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
2922 DCHECK(data_->kind() != ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)((void) 0);
2923 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
2924 broker()->mode());
2925 return object()->RawFastDoublePropertyAt(index);
2926 }
2927 JSObjectData* object_data = data()->AsJSObject();
2928 CHECK(index.is_inobject())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(index.is_inobject())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "index.is_inobject()"); } } while
(false);
2929 return object_data->GetInobjectField(index.property_index()).AsDouble();
2930}
2931
2932uint64_t JSObjectRef::RawFastDoublePropertyAsBitsAt(FieldIndex index) const {
2933 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
2934 DCHECK(data_->kind() != ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)((void) 0);
2935 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
2936 broker()->mode());
2937 return object()->RawFastDoublePropertyAsBitsAt(index);
2938 }
2939 JSObjectData* object_data = data()->AsJSObject();
2940 CHECK(index.is_inobject())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(index.is_inobject())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "index.is_inobject()"); } } while
(false);
2941 return object_data->GetInobjectField(index.property_index()).AsBitsOfDouble();
2942}
2943
2944ObjectRef JSObjectRef::RawFastPropertyAt(FieldIndex index) const {
2945 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
2946 DCHECK(data_->kind() != ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)((void) 0);
2947 AllowHandleAllocationIf allow_handle_allocation(data()->kind(),
2948 broker()->mode());
2949 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
2950 broker()->mode());
2951 return ObjectRef(broker(), handle(object()->RawFastPropertyAt(index),
2952 broker()->isolate()));
2953 }
2954 JSObjectData* object_data = data()->AsJSObject();
2955 CHECK(index.is_inobject())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(index.is_inobject())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "index.is_inobject()"); } } while
(false);
2956 return ObjectRef(
2957 broker(),
2958 object_data->GetInobjectField(index.property_index()).AsObject());
2959}
2960
2961bool AllocationSiteRef::IsFastLiteral() const {
2962 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
2963 DCHECK(data_->kind() != ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)((void) 0);
2964 AllowHeapAllocationIf allow_heap_allocation(
2965 data()->kind(), broker()->mode()); // For TryMigrateInstance.
2966 AllowHandleAllocationIf allow_handle_allocation(data()->kind(),
2967 broker()->mode());
2968 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
2969 broker()->mode());
2970 return IsInlinableFastLiteral(
2971 handle(object()->boilerplate(), broker()->isolate()));
2972 }
2973 return data()->AsAllocationSite()->IsFastLiteral();
2974}

2976void AllocationSiteRef::SerializeBoilerplate() {
2977 CHECK_EQ(broker()->mode(), JSHeapBroker::kSerializing)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(broker()->mode())>::type
, typename ::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(JSHeapBroker
::kSerializing)>::type>((broker()->mode()), (JSHeapBroker
::kSerializing)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))
) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "broker()->mode()" " " "=="
" " "JSHeapBroker::kSerializing"); } } while (false); } while
(false);
2978 data()->AsAllocationSite()->SerializeBoilerplate(broker());

2985
2986void JSObjectRef::EnsureElementsTenured() {
2987 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
2988 DCHECK(data_->kind() != ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)((void) 0);
2989 AllowHandleAllocationIf allow_handle_allocation(data()->kind(),
2990 broker()->mode());
2991 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
2992 broker()->mode());
2993 AllowHeapAllocationIf allow_heap_allocation(data()->kind(),
2994 broker()->mode());
2995
2996 Handle<FixedArrayBase> object_elements = elements().object();
2997 if (ObjectInYoungGeneration(*object_elements)) {
2998 // If we would like to pretenure a fixed cow array, we must ensure that
2999 // the array is already in old space, otherwise we'll create too many
3000 // old-to-new-space pointers (overflowing the store buffer).
3001 object_elements =
3002 broker()->isolate()->factory()->CopyAndTenureFixedCOWArray(
3003 Handle<FixedArray>::cast(object_elements));
3004 object()->set_elements(*object_elements);
3005 }
3006 return;
3007 }
3008 CHECK(data()->AsJSObject()->cow_or_empty_elements_tenured())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(data()->AsJSObject()->cow_or_empty_elements_tenured
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "data()->AsJSObject()->cow_or_empty_elements_tenured()"
); } } while (false);
3009}

3254// Accessors for direct heap reads.
3255#define DIRECT_HEAP_ACCESSOR_C(holder, result, name)result holderRef::name() const { return object()->name(); } \
3256 result holder##Ref::name() const { return object()->name(); }
3257
3258#define IF_ACCESS_FROM_HEAP_C(holder, name) \
3259 if (data_->should_access_heap()) { \
3260 CHECK(broker()->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kDisabled || \do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(broker()->mode() == JSHeapBroker
::kDisabled || ReadOnlyHeap::Contains(HeapObject::cast(*object
())))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "broker()->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kDisabled || ReadOnlyHeap::Contains(HeapObject::cast(*object()))"
); } } while (false)
3261 ReadOnlyHeap::Contains(HeapObject::cast(*object())))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(broker()->mode() == JSHeapBroker
::kDisabled || ReadOnlyHeap::Contains(HeapObject::cast(*object
())))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "broker()->mode() == JSHeapBroker::kDisabled || ReadOnlyHeap::Contains(HeapObject::cast(*object()))"
); } } while (false); \
3262 AllowHandleAllocationIf handle_allocation(data_->kind(), \
3263 broker()->mode()); \
3264 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data_->kind(), \
3265 broker()->mode()); \
3266 return object()->name(); \
3267 }
3268
3269#define IF_ACCESS_FROM_HEAP(holder, result, name) \
3270 if (data_->kind() == ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedHeapObject) { \
3271 AllowHandleAllocationIf handle_allocation(data_->kind(), \
3272 broker()->mode()); \
3273 AllowHandleDereferenceIf handle_dereference(data_->kind(), \
3274 broker()->mode()); \
3275 return result##Ref(broker(), \
3276 handle(object()->name(), broker()->isolate())); \
3277 } else if (data_->kind() == \
3278 ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject) { \
3279 AllowHandleDereferenceIf handle_dereference(data_->kind(), \
3280 broker()->mode()); \
3281 return result##Ref(broker(), broker()->GetRootHandle(object()->name())); \
3282 }
3283
3284// Macros for definining a const getter that, depending on the broker mode,
3285// either looks into the handle or into the serialized data.
3286#define BIMODAL_ACCESSOR(holder, result, name) \
3287 result##Ref holder##Ref::name() const { \
3288 IF_ACCESS_FROM_HEAP(holder, result, name); \
3289 ObjectData* data = ObjectRef::data()->As##holder()->name(); \
3290 if (data->kind() == ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedHeapObject) { \
3291 return result##Ref(broker(), data->object()); \
3292 } else { \
3293 return result##Ref(broker(), ObjectRef::data()->As##holder()->name()); \
3294 } \
3295 }
3296
3297// Like above except that the result type is not an XYZRef.
3298#define BIMODAL_ACCESSOR_C(holder, result, name) \
3299 result holder##Ref::name() const { \
3300 IF_ACCESS_FROM_HEAP_C(holder, name); \
3301 return ObjectRef::data()->As##holder()->name(); \
3302 }
3303
3304// Like above but for BitFields.
3305#define BIMODAL_ACCESSOR_B(holder, field, name, BitField) \
3306 typename BitField::FieldType holder##Ref::name() const { \
3307 IF_ACCESS_FROM_HEAP_C(holder, name); \
3308 return BitField::decode(ObjectRef::data()->As##holder()->field()); \
3309 }

3394base::Optional<CallHandlerInfoRef> FunctionTemplateInfoRef::call_code() const {
3395 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
3396 DCHECK(data_->kind() != ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)((void) 0);

3435HolderLookupResult FunctionTemplateInfoRef::LookupHolderOfExpectedType(
3436 MapRef receiver_map, SerializationPolicy policy) {
3437 const HolderLookupResult not_found;
3438
3439 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
3440 DCHECK(data_->kind() != ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)((void) 0);
3441 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
3442 broker()->mode());
3443 AllowHandleAllocationIf allow_handle_allocation(data()->kind(),
3444 broker()->mode());
3445
3446 CallOptimization call_optimization(broker()->isolate(), object());
3447 Handle<Map> receiver_map_ref(receiver_map.object());
3448 if (!receiver_map_ref->IsJSReceiverMap() ||
3449 (receiver_map_ref->is_access_check_needed() &&
3450 !object()->accept_any_receiver())) {
3451 return not_found;
3452 }
3453
3454 HolderLookupResult result;
3455 Handle<JSObject> holder = call_optimization.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(
3456 receiver_map_ref, &result.lookup);
3457
3458 switch (result.lookup) {
3459 case CallOptimization::kHolderFound:
3460 result.holder = JSObjectRef(broker(), holder);
3461 break;
3462 default:
3463 DCHECK_EQ(result.holder, base::nullopt)((void) 0);
3464 break;
3465 }
3466 return result;
3467 }
3468
3469 FunctionTemplateInfoData* fti_data = data()->AsFunctionTemplateInfo();
3470 KnownReceiversMap::iterator lookup_it =
3471 fti_data->known_receivers().find(receiver_map.data()->AsMap());
3472 if (lookup_it != fti_data->known_receivers().cend()) {
3473 return lookup_it->second;
3474 }
3475 if (policy == SerializationPolicy::kAssumeSerialized) {
3476 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(),do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "holder for receiver with map "
<< receiver_map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-heap-broker.cc"
<< ":" << 3477 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
3477 "holder for receiver with map " << receiver_map)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "holder for receiver with map "
<< receiver_map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-heap-broker.cc"
<< ":" << 3477 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
3478 return not_found;
3479 }
3480 if (!receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap() ||
3481 (receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() && !accept_any_receiver())) {
3482 fti_data->known_receivers().insert(
3483 {receiver_map.data()->AsMap(), not_found});
3484 return not_found;
3485 }
3486
3487 HolderLookupResult result;
3488 CallOptimization call_optimization(broker()->isolate(), object());
3489 Handle<JSObject> holder = call_optimization.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(
3490 receiver_map.object(), &result.lookup);
3491
3492 switch (result.lookup) {
3493 case CallOptimization::kHolderFound: {
3494 result.holder = JSObjectRef(broker(), holder);
3495 fti_data->known_receivers().insert(
3496 {receiver_map.data()->AsMap(), result});
3497 break;
3498 }
3499 default: {
3500 DCHECK_EQ(result.holder, base::nullopt)((void) 0);
3501 fti_data->known_receivers().insert(
3502 {receiver_map.data()->AsMap(), result});

3504 }

3781Maybe<double> ObjectRef::OddballToNumber() const {
3782 OddballType type = AsHeapObject().map().oddball_type();
3783
3784 switch (type) {
3785 case OddballType::kBoolean: {
3786 ObjectRef true_ref(broker(),
3787 broker()->isolate()->factory()->true_value());
3788 return this->equals(true_ref) ? Just(1.0) : Just(0.0);
3789 break;
3790 }
3791 case OddballType::kUndefined: {
3792 return Just(std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN());
3793 break;
3794 }
3795 case OddballType::kNull: {
3796 return Just(0.0);
3797 break;
3798 }
3799 default: {
3800 return Nothing<double>();
3801 break;
3802 }
3803 }

3806base::Optional<ObjectRef> ObjectRef::GetOwnConstantElement(
3807 uint32_t index, SerializationPolicy policy) const {
3808 if (data_->kind() == ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedHeapObject) {
3809 return (IsJSObject() || IsString())
3810 ? GetOwnElementFromHeap(broker(), object(), index, true)
3811 : base::nullopt;
3812 } else if (data_->kind() == ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject) {
3813 DCHECK(!IsJSObject())((void) 0);
3814 // TODO(mythria): For ReadOnly strings, currently we cannot access data from
3815 // heap without creating handles since we use LookupIterator. We should have
3816 // a custom implementation for read only strings that doesn't create
3817 // handles. Till then it is OK to disable this optimization since this only
3818 // impacts keyed accesses on read only strings.
3819 return base::nullopt;
3820 }
3821 ObjectData* element = nullptr;
3822 if (IsJSObject()) {
3823 element =
3824 data()->AsJSObject()->GetOwnConstantElement(broker(), index, policy);
3825 } else if (IsString()) {
3826 element = data()->AsString()->GetCharAsString(broker(), index, policy);
3827 }
3828 if (element == nullptr) return base::nullopt;
3829 return ObjectRef(broker(), element);
3830}

3924 entry->value = broker->zone()->New<ObjectData>(
3925 broker, storage, object,
3926 object->IsSmi() ? kSmi : kUnserializedHeapObject);

3929 break;

3933 }

→

←
Taking true branch
→

3942namespace {
3943OddballType GetOddballType(Isolate* isolate, Map map) {
3944 if (map.instance_type() != ODDBALL_TYPE) {
3945 return OddballType::kNone;
3946 }
3947 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
3948 if (map == roots.undefined_map()) {
3949 return OddballType::kUndefined;
3950 }
3951 if (map == roots.null_map()) {
3952 return OddballType::kNull;
3953 }
3954 if (map == roots.boolean_map()) {
3955 return OddballType::kBoolean;
3956 }
3957 if (map == roots.the_hole_map()) {
3958 return OddballType::kHole;
3959 }
3960 if (map == roots.uninitialized_map()) {
3961 return OddballType::kUninitialized;
3962 }
3963 DCHECK(map == roots.termination_exception_map() ||((void) 0)
3964 map == roots.arguments_marker_map() ||((void) 0)
3965 map == roots.optimized_out_map() || map == roots.stale_register_map())((void) 0);
3966 return OddballType::kOther;
3967}
3968} // namespace
3969
3970HeapObjectType HeapObjectRef::GetHeapObjectType() const {
3971 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
3972 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
3973 broker()->mode());
3974 Map map = Handle<HeapObject>::cast(object())->map();
3975 HeapObjectType::Flags flags(0);
3976 if (map.is_undetectable()) flags |= HeapObjectType::kUndetectable;
3977 if (map.is_callable()) flags |= HeapObjectType::kCallable;
3978 return HeapObjectType(map.instance_type(), flags,
3979 GetOddballType(broker()->isolate(), map));
3980 }
3981 HeapObjectType::Flags flags(0);
3982 if (map().is_undetectable()) flags |= HeapObjectType::kUndetectable;
3983 if (map().is_callable()) flags |= HeapObjectType::kCallable;
3984 return HeapObjectType(map().instance_type(), flags, map().oddball_type());
3985}

4130ObjectData* ObjectRef::data() const {
4131 switch (broker()->mode()) {
4132 case JSHeapBroker::kDisabled:
4133 CHECK_NE(data_->kind(), kSerializedHeapObject)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpNEImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(data_->kind())>::type, typename
::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(kSerializedHeapObject
)>::type>((data_->kind()), (kSerializedHeapObject));
do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s."
, "data_->kind()" " " "!=" " " "kSerializedHeapObject"); }
} while (false); } while (false);
4134 return data_;
4135 case JSHeapBroker::kSerializing:
4136 CHECK_NE(data_->kind(), kUnserializedHeapObject)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpNEImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(data_->kind())>::type, typename
::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(kUnserializedHeapObject
)>::type>((data_->kind()), (kUnserializedHeapObject)
); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s."
, "data_->kind()" " " "!=" " " "kUnserializedHeapObject");
} } while (false); } while (false);
4137 return data_;
4138 case JSHeapBroker::kSerialized:
4139#ifdef DEBUG
4140 data_->used_status = ObjectData::Usage::kDataUsed;
4141#endif // DEBUG
4142 CHECK_NE(data_->kind(), kUnserializedHeapObject)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpNEImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(data_->kind())>::type, typename
::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(kUnserializedHeapObject
)>::type>((data_->kind()), (kUnserializedHeapObject)
); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s."
, "data_->kind()" " " "!=" " " "kUnserializedHeapObject");
} } while (false); } while (false);
4143 return data_;
4144 case JSHeapBroker::kRetired:
4145 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
4146 }

4213JSArrayRef SharedFunctionInfoRef::GetTemplateObject(
4214 TemplateObjectDescriptionRef description, FeedbackSource const& source,
4215 SerializationPolicy policy) {
4216 // First, see if we have processed feedback from the vector, respecting
4217 // the serialization policy.
4218 ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
4219 policy == SerializationPolicy::kSerializeIfNeeded
4220 ? broker()->ProcessFeedbackForTemplateObject(source)
4221 : broker()->GetFeedbackForTemplateObject(source);
4222
4223 if (!feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
4224 return feedback.AsTemplateObject().value();
4225 }
4226
4227 if (data_->should_access_heap()) {
4228 DCHECK(data_->kind() != ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject)((void) 0);
4229 AllowHandleAllocationIf allow_handle_allocation(data()->kind(),
4230 broker()->mode());
4231 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(data()->kind(),
4232 broker()->mode());
4233 Handle<JSArray> template_object =
4234 TemplateObjectDescription::GetTemplateObject(
4235 isolate(), broker()->target_native_context().object(),
4236 description.object(), object(), source.slot.ToInt());
4237 return JSArrayRef(broker(), template_object);
4238 }
4239
4240 JSArrayData* array =
4241 data()->AsSharedFunctionInfo()->GetTemplateObject(source.slot);
4242 if (array != nullptr) return JSArrayRef(broker(), array);
4243
4244 CHECK_EQ(policy, SerializationPolicy::kSerializeIfNeeded)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(policy)>::type, typename ::
v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(SerializationPolicy::
kSerializeIfNeeded)>::type>((policy), (SerializationPolicy
::kSerializeIfNeeded)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)
), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "policy" " " "==" " "
"SerializationPolicy::kSerializeIfNeeded"); } } while (false
); } while (false);
4245 CHECK(broker()->SerializingAllowed())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(broker()->SerializingAllowed
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "broker()->SerializingAllowed()"
); } } while (false);
4246
4247 Handle<JSArray> template_object =
4248 TemplateObjectDescription::GetTemplateObject(
4249 broker()->isolate(), broker()->target_native_context().object(),
4250 description.object(), object(), source.slot.ToInt());
4251 array = broker()->GetOrCreateData(template_object)->AsJSArray();

::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(descriptor_index.as_int())>
::type, typename ::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(NumberOfOwnDescriptors
())>::type>((descriptor_index.as_int()), (NumberOfOwnDescriptors
())); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal

4326 desc_array_data->contents().end();

4394 NameRef const& name, SerializationPolicy policy) const {

4398 }

4404}
4405
4406bool CanInlineElementAccess(MapRef const& map) {
4407 if (!map.IsJSObjectMap()) return false;
4408 if (map.is_access_check_needed()) return false;
4409 if (map.has_indexed_interceptor()) return false;
4410 ElementsKind const elements_kind = map.elements_kind();
4411 if (IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind)) return true;
4412 if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind) &&
4413 elements_kind != BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS &&
4414 elements_kind != BIGINT64_ELEMENTS) {
4415 return true;
4416 }
4417 return false;
4418}

4420ProcessedFeedback::ProcessedFeedback(Kind kind, FeedbackSlotKind slot_kind)
4421 : kind_(kind), slot_kind_(slot_kind) {}

4423KeyedAccessMode ElementAccessFeedback::keyed_mode() const {
4424 return keyed_mode_;
4425}
4426
4427ZoneVector<ElementAccessFeedback::TransitionGroup> const&
4428ElementAccessFeedback::transition_groups() const {
4429 return transition_groups_;
4430}
4431
4432ElementAccessFeedback const& ElementAccessFeedback::Refine(
4433 ZoneVector<Handle<Map>> const& inferred_maps, Zone* zone) const {
4434 ElementAccessFeedback& refined_feedback =
4435 *zone->New<ElementAccessFeedback>(zone, keyed_mode(), slot_kind());
4436 if (inferred_maps.empty()) return refined_feedback;
4437
4438 ZoneUnorderedSet<Handle<Map>, Handle<Map>::hash, Handle<Map>::equal_to>
4439 inferred(zone);
4440 inferred.insert(inferred_maps.begin(), inferred_maps.end());
4441
4442 for (auto const& group : transition_groups()) {
4443 DCHECK(!group.empty())((void) 0);
4444 TransitionGroup new_group(zone);
4445 for (size_t i = 1; i < group.size(); ++i) {
4446 Handle<Map> source = group[i];
4447 if (inferred.find(source) != inferred.end()) {
4448 new_group.push_back(source);
4449 }
4450 }
4451
4452 Handle<Map> target = group.front();
4453 bool const keep_target =
4454 inferred.find(target) != inferred.end() || new_group.size() > 1;
4455 if (keep_target) {
4456 new_group.push_back(target);
4457 // The target must be at the front, the order of sources doesn't matter.
4458 std::swap(new_group[0], new_group[new_group.size() - 1]);
4459 }
4460
4461 if (!new_group.empty()) {
4462 DCHECK(new_group.size() == 1 || new_group.front().equals(target))((void) 0);
4463 refined_feedback.transition_groups_.push_back(std::move(new_group));
4464 }
4465 }
4466 return refined_feedback;
4467}

4499bool GlobalAccessFeedback::IsMegamorphic() const {
4500 return !cell_or_context_.has_value();
4501}

while (false);

4525base::Optional<ObjectRef> GlobalAccessFeedback::GetConstantHint() const {
4526 if (IsPropertyCell()) {
4527 return property_cell().value();
4528 } else if (IsScriptContextSlot() && immutable()) {
4529 return script_context().get(slot_index());
4530 } else {
4531 return base::nullopt;
4532 }

4534
4535KeyedAccessMode KeyedAccessMode::FromNexus(FeedbackNexus const& nexus) {
4536 FeedbackSlotKind kind = nexus.kind();
4537 if (IsKeyedLoadICKind(kind)) {
4538 return KeyedAccessMode(AccessMode::kLoad, nexus.GetKeyedAccessLoadMode());
4539 }
4540 if (IsKeyedHasICKind(kind)) {
4541 return KeyedAccessMode(AccessMode::kHas, nexus.GetKeyedAccessLoadMode());
4542 }
4543 if (IsKeyedStoreICKind(kind)) {
4544 return KeyedAccessMode(AccessMode::kStore, nexus.GetKeyedAccessStoreMode());
4545 }
4546 if (IsStoreInArrayLiteralICKind(kind) ||
4547 IsStoreDataPropertyInLiteralKind(kind)) {
4548 return KeyedAccessMode(AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral,
4549 nexus.GetKeyedAccessStoreMode());
4550 }
4551 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
4552}
4553
4554AccessMode KeyedAccessMode::access_mode() const { return access_mode_; }
4555
4556bool KeyedAccessMode::IsLoad() const {
4557 return access_mode_ == AccessMode::kLoad || access_mode_ == AccessMode::kHas;
4558}
4559bool KeyedAccessMode::IsStore() const {
4560 return access_mode_ == AccessMode::kStore ||
4561 access_mode_ == AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral;
4562}

, "IsLoad()"); } } while (false);

4567}

4569KeyedAccessStoreMode KeyedAccessMode::store_mode() const {

4572}

("Check failed: %s.", "!IsStore()"); } } while (false);

, "IsLoad()"); } } while (false);
4584}

4587 : access_mode_(access_mode), load_store_mode_(store_mode) {
4588 CHECK(!IsLoad())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!IsLoad())), 0))) { V8_Fatal(
"Check failed: %s.", "!IsLoad()"); } } while (false);
4589 CHECK(IsStore())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(IsStore())), 0))) { V8_Fatal(
"Check failed: %s.", "IsStore()"); } } while (false);
4590}

4604bool ElementAccessFeedback::HasOnlyStringMaps(JSHeapBroker* broker) const {
4605 for (auto const& group : transition_groups()) {
4606 for (Handle<Map> map : group) {
4607 if (!MapRef(broker, map).IsStringMap()) return false;
4608 }
4609 }
4610 return true;
4611}

4634
4635void JSHeapBroker::SetFeedback(FeedbackSource const& source,
4636 ProcessedFeedback const* feedback) {
4637 CHECK(source.IsValid())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(source.IsValid())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "source.IsValid()"); } } while (false);
4638 auto insertion = feedback_.insert({source, feedback});
4639 CHECK(insertion.second)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(insertion.second)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "insertion.second"); } } while (false);
4640}
4641
4642bool JSHeapBroker::HasFeedback(FeedbackSource const& source) const {
4643 DCHECK(source.IsValid())((void) 0);
4644 return feedback_.find(source) != feedback_.end();
4645}
4646
4647ProcessedFeedback const& JSHeapBroker::GetFeedback(
4648 FeedbackSource const& source) const {
4649 DCHECK(source.IsValid())((void) 0);
4650 auto it = feedback_.find(source);
4651 CHECK_NE(it, feedback_.end())do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpNEImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(it)>::type, typename ::v8::
base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(feedback_.end())>::type
>((it), (feedback_.end())); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(
!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "it" " " "!=" " "
"feedback_.end()"); } } while (false); } while (false);
4652 return *it->second;
4653}
4654
4655FeedbackSlotKind JSHeapBroker::GetFeedbackSlotKind(
4656 FeedbackSource const& source) const {
4657 if (is_concurrent_inlining_) {
4658 ProcessedFeedback const& processed = GetFeedback(source);
4659 return processed.slot_kind();
4660 }
4661 FeedbackNexus nexus(source.vector, source.slot);
4662 return nexus.kind();
4663}
4664
4665bool JSHeapBroker::FeedbackIsInsufficient(FeedbackSource const& source) const {
4666 return is_concurrent_inlining_
4667 ? GetFeedback(source).IsInsufficient()
4668 : FeedbackNexus(source.vector, source.slot).IsUninitialized();
4669}
4670
4671namespace {
4672// Remove unupdatable and abandoned prototype maps in-place.
4673void FilterRelevantReceiverMaps(Isolate* isolate, MapHandles* maps) {
4674 auto in = maps->begin();
4675 auto out = in;
4676 auto end = maps->end();
4677
4678 for (; in != end; ++in) {
4679 Handle<Map> map = *in;
4680 if (Map::TryUpdate(isolate, map).ToHandle(&map) &&
4681 !map->is_abandoned_prototype_map()) {
4682 DCHECK(!map->is_deprecated())((void) 0);
4683 *out = *in;
4684 ++out;
4685 }
4686 }
4687
4688 // Remove everything between the last valid map and the end of the vector.
4689 maps->erase(out, end);
4690}
4691
4692MaybeObjectHandle TryGetMinimorphicHandler(
4693 std::vector<MapAndHandler> const& maps_and_handlers,
4694 FeedbackSlotKind kind) {
4695 if (!FLAG_dynamic_map_checks || !IsLoadICKind(kind))
4696 return MaybeObjectHandle();
4697
4698 MaybeObjectHandle initial_handler;
4699 for (MapAndHandler map_and_handler : maps_and_handlers) {
4700 auto map = map_and_handler.first;
4701 MaybeObjectHandle handler = map_and_handler.second;
4702 if (handler.is_null()) return MaybeObjectHandle();
4703 DCHECK(!handler->IsCleared())((void) 0);
4704 // TODO(mythria): extend this to DataHandlers too
4705 if (!handler.object()->IsSmi()) return MaybeObjectHandle();
4706 if (LoadHandler::GetHandlerKind(handler.object()->ToSmi()) !=
4707 LoadHandler::Kind::kField) {
4708 return MaybeObjectHandle();
4709 }
4710 CHECK(!map->IsJSGlobalProxyMap())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!map->IsJSGlobalProxyMap()
)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "!map->IsJSGlobalProxyMap()"
); } } while (false);
4711 if (initial_handler.is_null()) {
4712 initial_handler = handler;
4713 } else if (!handler.is_identical_to(initial_handler)) {
4714 return MaybeObjectHandle();
4715 }
4716 }
4717 return initial_handler;
4718}
4719
4720bool HasMigrationTargets(const MapHandles& maps) {
4721 for (Handle<Map> map : maps) {
4722 if (map->is_migration_target()) return true;
4723 }
4724 return false;
4725}
4726} // namespace
4727
4728bool JSHeapBroker::CanUseFeedback(const FeedbackNexus& nexus) const {
4729 // TODO(jgruber,v8:8888): Currently, nci code does not use any
4730 // feedback. This restriction will be relaxed in the future.
4731 return !is_native_context_independent() && !nexus.IsUninitialized();
4732}
4733
4734const ProcessedFeedback& JSHeapBroker::NewInsufficientFeedback(
4735 FeedbackSlotKind kind) const {
4736 return *zone()->New<InsufficientFeedback>(kind);
4737}
4738
4739ProcessedFeedback const& JSHeapBroker::ReadFeedbackForPropertyAccess(
4740 FeedbackSource const& source, AccessMode mode,
4741 base::Optional<NameRef> static_name) {
4742 FeedbackNexus nexus(source.vector, source.slot);
4743 FeedbackSlotKind kind = nexus.kind();
4744 if (!CanUseFeedback(nexus)) return NewInsufficientFeedback(kind);
4745
4746 std::vector<MapAndHandler> maps_and_handlers;
4747 nexus.ExtractMapsAndFeedback(&maps_and_handlers);
4748 MapHandles maps;
4749 for (auto const& entry : maps_and_handlers) {
4750 maps.push_back(entry.first);
4751 }
4752
4753 base::Optional<NameRef> name =
4754 static_name.has_value() ? static_name : GetNameFeedback(nexus);
4755 MaybeObjectHandle handler = TryGetMinimorphicHandler(maps_and_handlers, kind);
4756 if (!handler.is_null()) {
4757 return *zone()->New<MinimorphicLoadPropertyAccessFeedback>(
4758 *name, kind, nexus.ic_state() == MONOMORPHIC, handler.object(),
4759 HasMigrationTargets(maps));
4760 }
4761
4762 FilterRelevantReceiverMaps(isolate(), &maps);
4763
4764 // If no maps were found for a non-megamorphic access, then our maps died
4765 // and we should soft-deopt.
4766 if (maps.empty() && nexus.ic_state() != MEGAMORPHIC) {
4767 return NewInsufficientFeedback(kind);
4768 }
4769
4770 if (name.has_value()) {
4771 // We rely on this invariant in JSGenericLowering.
4772 DCHECK_IMPLIES(maps.empty(), nexus.ic_state() == MEGAMORPHIC)((void) 0);
4773 return *zone()->New<NamedAccessFeedback>(
4774 *name, ZoneVector<Handle<Map>>(maps.begin(), maps.end(), zone()), kind);
4775 } else if (nexus.GetKeyType() == ELEMENT && !maps.empty()) {
4776 return ProcessFeedbackMapsForElementAccess(
4777 maps, KeyedAccessMode::FromNexus(nexus), kind);
4778 } else {
4779 // No actionable feedback.
4780 DCHECK(maps.empty())((void) 0);
4781 DCHECK_EQ(nexus.ic_state(), MEGAMORPHIC)((void) 0);
4782 // TODO(neis): Using ElementAccessFeedback here is kind of an abuse.
4783 return *zone()->New<ElementAccessFeedback>(
4784 zone(), KeyedAccessMode::FromNexus(nexus), kind);
4785 }
4786}

5098
5099ElementAccessFeedback const& JSHeapBroker::ProcessFeedbackMapsForElementAccess(
5100 MapHandles const& maps, KeyedAccessMode const& keyed_mode,
5101 FeedbackSlotKind slot_kind) {
5102 DCHECK(!maps.empty())((void) 0);
5103
5104 // Collect possible transition targets.
5105 MapHandles possible_transition_targets;
5106 possible_transition_targets.reserve(maps.size());
5107 for (Handle<Map> map : maps) {
5108 MapRef map_ref(this, map);
5109 map_ref.SerializeRootMap();
5110
5111 if (CanInlineElementAccess(map_ref) &&
5112 IsFastElementsKind(map->elements_kind()) &&
5113 GetInitialFastElementsKind() != map->elements_kind()) {
5114 possible_transition_targets.push_back(map);
5115 }
5116 }
5117
5118 using TransitionGroup = ElementAccessFeedback::TransitionGroup;
5119 ZoneUnorderedMap<Handle<Map>, TransitionGroup, Handle<Map>::hash,
5120 Handle<Map>::equal_to>
5121 transition_groups(zone());
5122
5123 // Separate the actual receiver maps and the possible transition sources.
5124 for (Handle<Map> map : maps) {
5125 // Don't generate elements kind transitions from stable maps.
5126 Map transition_target = map->is_stable()
5127 ? Map()
5128 : map->FindElementsKindTransitionedMap(
5129 isolate(), possible_transition_targets);
5130 if (transition_target.is_null()) {
5131 TransitionGroup group(1, map, zone());
5132 transition_groups.insert({map, group});
5133 } else {
5134 Handle<Map> target(transition_target, isolate());
5135 TransitionGroup new_group(1, target, zone());
5136 TransitionGroup& actual_group =
5137 transition_groups.insert({target, new_group}).first->second;
5138 actual_group.push_back(map);
5139 }
5140 }
5141
5142 ElementAccessFeedback* result =
5143 zone()->New<ElementAccessFeedback>(zone(), keyed_mode, slot_kind);
5144 for (auto entry : transition_groups) {
5145 result->AddGroup(std::move(entry.second));
5146 }
5147
5148 CHECK(!result->transition_groups().empty())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!result->transition_groups
().empty())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "!result->transition_groups().empty()"
); } } while (false);
5149 return *result;
5150}
5151
5152void ElementAccessFeedback::AddGroup(TransitionGroup&& group) {
5153 CHECK(!group.empty())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!group.empty())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "!group.empty()"); } } while (false);
5154 transition_groups_.push_back(std::move(group));
5155
5156#ifdef ENABLE_SLOW_DCHECKS
5157 // Check that each of the group's maps occurs exactly once in the whole
5158 // feedback. This implies that "a source is not a target".
5159 for (Handle<Map> map : group) {
5160 int count = 0;
5161 for (TransitionGroup const& some_group : transition_groups()) {
5162 count += std::count_if(
5163 some_group.begin(), some_group.end(),
5164 [&](Handle<Map> some_map) { return some_map.equals(map); });
5165 }
5166 CHECK_EQ(count, 1)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(count)>::type, typename ::
v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(1)>::type>((count
), (1)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "count" " " "==" " " "1"); } } while (false
); } while (false);
5167 }
5168#endif
5169}
5170
5171std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, const ObjectRef& ref) {
5172 if (ref.data_->kind() == ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedHeapObject ||
5173 !FLAG_concurrent_recompilation) {
5174 // We cannot be in a background thread so it's safe to read the heap.
5175 AllowHandleDereference allow_handle_dereference;
5176 return os << ref.data() << " {" << ref.object() << "}";
5177 } else if (ref.data_->kind() ==
5178 ObjectDataKind::kUnserializedReadOnlyHeapObject) {
5179 AllowHandleDereferenceIf allow_handle_dereference(ref.data()->kind(),
5180 ref.broker()->mode());
5181 return os << ref.data() << " {" << ref.object() << "}";
5182 } else {
5183 return os << ref.data();
5184 }
5185}
5186
5187base::Optional<NameRef> JSHeapBroker::GetNameFeedback(
5188 FeedbackNexus const& nexus) {
5189 Name raw_name = nexus.GetName();
5190 if (raw_name.is_null()) return base::nullopt;
5191 return NameRef(this, handle(raw_name, isolate()));
5192}
5193
5194PropertyAccessInfo JSHeapBroker::GetPropertyAccessInfo(
5195 MapRef map, NameRef name, AccessMode access_mode,
5196 CompilationDependencies* dependencies, SerializationPolicy policy) {
5197 PropertyAccessTarget target({map, name, access_mode});
5198 auto it = property_access_infos_.find(target);
5199 if (it != property_access_infos_.end()) return it->second;
5200
5201 if (policy == SerializationPolicy::kAssumeSerialized) {
5202 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(this, "PropertyAccessInfo for "do { if (this->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} << this
->Trace() << "Missing " << "PropertyAccessInfo for "
<< access_mode << " of property " << name <<
" on map " << map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-heap-broker.cc"
<< ":" << 5204 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
5203 << access_mode << " of property " << namedo { if (this->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} << this
->Trace() << "Missing " << "PropertyAccessInfo for "
<< access_mode << " of property " << name <<
" on map " << map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-heap-broker.cc"
<< ":" << 5204 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
5204 << " on map " << map)do { if (this->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} << this
->Trace() << "Missing " << "PropertyAccessInfo for "
<< access_mode << " of property " << name <<
" on map " << map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-heap-broker.cc"
<< ":" << 5204 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
5205 return PropertyAccessInfo::Invalid(zone());
5206 }
5207
5208 CHECK_NOT_NULL(dependencies)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!((dependencies) != nullptr)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "(dependencies) != nullptr"
); } } while (false);
5209 AccessInfoFactory factory(this, dependencies, zone());
5210 PropertyAccessInfo access_info = factory.ComputePropertyAccessInfo(
5211 map.object(), name.object(), access_mode);
5212 if (is_concurrent_inlining_) {
5213 CHECK(SerializingAllowed())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(SerializingAllowed())), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "SerializingAllowed()"); } } while
(false);
5214 TRACE(this, "Storing PropertyAccessInfo for "
5215 << access_mode << " of property " << name << " on map "
5216 << map);
5217 property_access_infos_.insert({target, access_info});
5218 }
5219 return access_info;
5220}
5221
5222MinimorphicLoadPropertyAccessInfo JSHeapBroker::GetPropertyAccessInfo(
5223 MinimorphicLoadPropertyAccessFeedback const& feedback,
5224 FeedbackSource const& source, SerializationPolicy policy) {
5225 auto it = minimorphic_property_access_infos_.find(source.index());
5226 if (it != minimorphic_property_access_infos_.end()) return it->second;
5227
5228 if (policy == SerializationPolicy::kAssumeSerialized) {
5229 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(do { if (this->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} << this
->Trace() << "Missing " << "MinimorphicLoadPropertyAccessInfo for slot "
<< source.index() << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-heap-broker.cc"
<< ":" << 5230 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
5230 this, "MinimorphicLoadPropertyAccessInfo for slot " << source.index())do { if (this->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} << this
->Trace() << "Missing " << "MinimorphicLoadPropertyAccessInfo for slot "
<< source.index() << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-heap-broker.cc"
<< ":" << 5230 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
5231 return MinimorphicLoadPropertyAccessInfo::Invalid();
5232 }
5233
5234 AccessInfoFactory factory(this, nullptr, zone());
5235 MinimorphicLoadPropertyAccessInfo access_info =
5236 factory.ComputePropertyAccessInfo(feedback);
5237 if (is_concurrent_inlining_) {
5238 TRACE(this,
5239 "Storing MinimorphicLoadPropertyAccessInfo for " << source.index());
5240 minimorphic_property_access_infos_.insert({source.index(), access_info});
5241 }
5242 return access_info;
5243}

5305
5306BytecodeAnalysis const& JSHeapBroker::GetBytecodeAnalysis(
5307 Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecode_array, BailoutId osr_bailout_id,
5308 bool analyze_liveness, SerializationPolicy policy) {
5309 ObjectData* bytecode_array_data = GetOrCreateData(bytecode_array);
5310 CHECK_NOT_NULL(bytecode_array_data)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!((bytecode_array_data) != nullptr
)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "(bytecode_array_data) != nullptr"
); } } while (false);
5311
5312 auto it = bytecode_analyses_.find(bytecode_array_data);
5313 if (it != bytecode_analyses_.end()) {
5314 // Bytecode analysis can be run for OSR or for non-OSR. In the rare case
5315 // where we optimize for OSR and consider the top-level function itself for
5316 // inlining (because of recursion), we need both the OSR and the non-OSR
5317 // analysis. Fortunately, the only difference between the two lies in
5318 // whether the OSR entry offset gets computed (from the OSR bailout id).
5319 // Hence it's okay to reuse the OSR-version when asked for the non-OSR
5320 // version, such that we need to store at most one analysis result per
5321 // bytecode array.
5322 CHECK_IMPLIES(osr_bailout_id != it->second->osr_bailout_id(),do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!(osr_bailout_id != it->second
->osr_bailout_id()) || (osr_bailout_id.IsNone()))), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "osr_bailout_id != it->second->osr_bailout_id()"
" implies " "osr_bailout_id.IsNone()"); } } while (false)
5323 osr_bailout_id.IsNone())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!(osr_bailout_id != it->second
->osr_bailout_id()) || (osr_bailout_id.IsNone()))), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "osr_bailout_id != it->second->osr_bailout_id()"
" implies " "osr_bailout_id.IsNone()"); } } while (false);
5324 CHECK_EQ(analyze_liveness, it->second->liveness_analyzed())do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(analyze_liveness)>::type, typename
::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(it->second->
liveness_analyzed())>::type>((analyze_liveness), (it->
second->liveness_analyzed())); do { if ((__builtin_expect(
!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "analyze_liveness"
" " "==" " " "it->second->liveness_analyzed()"); } } while
(false); } while (false);
5325 return *it->second;
5326 }
5327
5328 CHECK_EQ(policy, SerializationPolicy::kSerializeIfNeeded)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(policy)>::type, typename ::
v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(SerializationPolicy::
kSerializeIfNeeded)>::type>((policy), (SerializationPolicy
::kSerializeIfNeeded)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)
), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "policy" " " "==" " "
"SerializationPolicy::kSerializeIfNeeded"); } } while (false
); } while (false);
5329 BytecodeAnalysis* analysis = zone()->New<BytecodeAnalysis>(
5330 bytecode_array, zone(), osr_bailout_id, analyze_liveness);
5331 DCHECK_EQ(analysis->osr_bailout_id(), osr_bailout_id)((void) 0);
5332 bytecode_analyses_[bytecode_array_data] = analysis;
5333 return *analysis;
5334}
